00:17:23.501 --> 00:17:26.670
here with the luscious Olivia "Don't
look at my tits. I have a mind" Morris.

246
00:17:26.754 --> 00:17:29.798
Here is my Woodsboro Massacre
anniversary question:

247
00:17:29.882 --> 00:17:31.758
What is your favorite
scary movie?

248
00:17:31.842 --> 00:17:34.261
Is that all you've got?
Some stupid douche question?

249
00:17:34.345 --> 00:17:36.304
Yeah.
where'd you hear that anyways?

250
00:17:36.389 --> 00:17:38.723
It's a line from "Stab One." duh.
Hey. Charlie.

251
00:17:38.808 --> 00:17:42.018
You're a. a genre nut. Kirby.
What's your favorite scary movie?

252
00:17:42.103 --> 00:17:43.395
"Bambi."

253
00:17:43.479 --> 00:17:45.647
Dork. What?

254
00:17:45.731 --> 00:17:47.607
That's funny. Kirby.

255
00:17:49.443 --> 00:17:53.238
- Completely unaware you exist.
- No. man. she wants me.

256
00:17:55.950 --> 00:17:58.785
Yeah. I wish. right?
Asshole.

257
00:17:58.869 --> 00:18:01.204
I think Charlie likes you.

258
00:18:01.289 --> 00:18:03.081
And I like him.

259
00:18:03.165 --> 00:18:06.042
To tease. to torment.
to make him squirm.

260
00:18:06.127 --> 00:18:09.129
You could do a lot worse.
trust me.

261
00:18:11.382 --> 00:18:14.467
Hi. Trevor. Bye. Trevor.

262
00:18:14.552 --> 00:18:17.012
Can we talk?

263
00:18:17.096 --> 00:18:20.432
Somebody cares about you over here.
you know?

264
00:18:20.516 --> 00:18:23.143
Someone who made you
really happy once.

265
00:18:23.227 --> 00:18:25.478
Someone who never
should have let you go.

266
00:18:25.563 --> 00:18:29.399
When you're done with a phone call.
you let someone go.

267
00:18:29.483 --> 00:18:32.193
Or when you take someone to the airport.
you let them go.

268
00:18:32.278 --> 00:18:35.405
When you tell someone you love her.
she gives you everything.

269
00:18:35.489 --> 00:18:37.240
and then you just go out
with someone else.

270
00:18:37.325 --> 00:18:39.284
that is not letting her go.
that's dumping her. okay?

271
00:18:39.368 --> 00:18:42.287
That's... that's betrayal.

272
00:18:43.331 --> 00:18:44.891
Trevor Sheldon.

273
00:18:44.915 --> 00:18:47.584
denied live on "Hall Pass"
with Robbie Mercer.

274
00:18:47.668 --> 00:18:49.586
What is your favorite
scary movie. man?

275
00:18:49.670 --> 00:18:51.763
I'll show you.

276
00:18:58.220 --> 00:19:01.348
And I began to believe myself
that that was all I was.

277
00:19:01.432 --> 00:19:06.269
a victim.
and that was unacceptable to me.

278
00:19:06.354 --> 00:19:09.939
So. I sat down...

279
00:19:10.024 --> 00:19:13.443
and began to write
a new role that would be my own.

280
00:19:13.527 --> 00:19:16.780
a role for a woman who could leave
the walls of fear behind

281
00:19:16.864 --> 00:19:20.241
and step out into the sunlight.
out of darkness.

282
00:19:20.326 --> 00:19:23.370
Thank you.

283
00:19:23.454 --> 00:19:26.414
Okay. we're gonna start
the book signing in a sec.

284
00:19:26.499 --> 00:19:30.210
So buy your copies while they last.
Lookin' at you. ladies.

285
00:19:30.294 --> 00:19:34.464
New York Times bestseller.
Rave reviews.

286
00:19:34.548 --> 00:19:37.050
Gale.
I'm glad you came.

287
00:19:37.134 --> 00:19:38.176
Congratulations. Sidney.

288
00:19:38.260 --> 00:19:40.762
I haven't had a chance
to read it yet. but...

289
00:19:40.846 --> 00:19:43.973
I know where you can get one.

290
00:19:45.309 --> 00:19:48.687
Dewey! Hey!

291
00:19:48.771 --> 00:19:50.939
Hey. Sid.
Gale. you made it.

292
00:19:51.023 --> 00:19:52.691
What are you doing here?

293
00:19:52.775 --> 00:19:54.859
Sid. I'm sorry.
I gotta do something here.

294
00:19:54.944 --> 00:19:56.861
- Shit!
- I'm really sorry.

295
00:19:56.946 --> 00:19:59.322
Excuse me!
This will only take a minute.

296
00:19:59.407 --> 00:20:02.659
I need you all to stay where you are
and remain silent.

297
00:20:02.743 --> 00:20:04.452
Nobody leaves yet.
The Sheriff thanks you.

298
00:20:04.537 --> 00:20:06.830
Can this wait. Barney Fife?
I'm running an event here.

299
00:20:06.914 --> 00:20:09.833
- Ma'am. this is a police event now.
- What's going on?

300
00:20:09.917 --> 00:20:12.585
Gale. this is police business.
If you could just let us handle this.

301
00:20:12.670 --> 00:20:15.463
I'm talking to my husband.
Deputy Judy.

302
00:20:15.548 --> 00:20:17.424
Listen. there's a phone we believe

303
00:20:17.508 --> 00:20:19.426
may have been taken
from the scene of a crime.

304
00:20:19.510 --> 00:20:23.263
Deputy Hicks has traced its location
back to these coordinates.

305
00:20:23.347 --> 00:20:25.181
The rest is need-to-know.

306
00:20:25.266 --> 00:20:28.810
- And I'm not "need-to-know"?
- Shh.

307
00:20:28.894 --> 00:20:31.104
Hoss. I'm hearing something.

308
00:20:31.188 --> 00:20:33.481
Sheriff. it's ringing out here!

309
00:20:37.061 --> 00:20:38.186
There!

310
00:20:43.868 --> 00:20:45.952
- It's coming from the trunk.
- There.

311
00:20:46.036 --> 00:20:48.705
Dewey?
Gonna need everyone to stay back.

312
00:20:48.789 --> 00:20:51.124
- Not now. Sid.
- It's my rental.

313
00:21:00.760 --> 00:21:03.178
Okay.
it's now an official crime scene.

314
00:21:03.262 --> 00:21:05.013
Let's lock it down.
Get that camera outta here!

315
00:21:05.097 --> 00:21:07.640
- Everybody back.
- Gimme that camera.

316
00:21:07.725 --> 00:21:09.768
Please tell me this is a prank.
Dewey.

317
00:21:09.852 --> 00:21:12.270
- I'm afraid not. Sid.
- On the curb. ma'am.

318
00:21:12.354 --> 00:21:14.147
- Come on.
- Everybody. get back!

319
00:21:14.231 --> 00:21:16.441
Henry. you're not gonna believe
what just happened.

320
00:21:16.525 --> 00:21:18.485
Stand back. Gale. Gale.

321
00:21:18.569 --> 00:21:20.236
I just wanna see.

322
00:21:20.321 --> 00:21:22.280
Cover up your kid's eyes!

323
00:21:22.364 --> 00:21:25.617
Okay.
essays are due Tuesday.

324
00:21:25.701 --> 00:21:28.369
"Why Woodsboro is the best..."

325
00:21:28.454 --> 00:21:32.624
Anything with an on/off switch
should be off. that's the rule!

326
00:21:32.708 --> 00:21:35.084
Somebody wanna share?

327
00:21:35.169 --> 00:21:37.754
Jenny Randall and Marnie Cooper
were murdered last night.

328
00:21:37.838 --> 00:21:39.923
- What?
- What?

329
00:21:40.007 --> 00:21:41.341
Stabbed to death.

330
00:21:41.425 --> 00:21:43.760
- What's your favorite scary...
- Shut up!

331
00:21:43.844 --> 00:21:46.763
- Yo. it's a news van!
- Class is not over!

332
00:21:46.847 --> 00:21:48.139
That was fast.

333
00:21:48.224 --> 00:21:51.760
This week marks the anniversary
of the infamous Woodsboro Murders.

334
00:21:51.784 --> 00:21:56.746
Two girls killed the exact day
local celebrity victim Sidney Prescott

335
00:21:56.991 --> 00:21:58.742
chose to return to her hometown.

336
00:21:58.926 --> 00:22:01.511
It all could be something right out
of a Gale Weathers best-seller.

337
00:22:01.595 --> 00:22:03.179
And where is she now?

338
00:22:03.364 --> 00:22:04.739
Well. living right here in Woodsboro...

339
00:22:04.824 --> 00:22:07.408
- Mrs. Riley.
- Hoss.

340
00:22:07.493 --> 00:22:09.753
- First Lady.
- Perkins.

341
00:22:10.538 --> 00:22:12.622
Excuse me. Gale.
He's conducting an interview.

342
00:22:12.706 --> 00:22:14.207
Great.
I love interviews.

343
00:22:14.291 --> 00:22:16.960
You'll have to wait. Gale.
Sorry. can't let you in there.

344
00:22:17.044 --> 00:22:20.547
What are you gonna do.
arrest me. Deputy Judy?

345
00:22:20.631 --> 00:22:21.923
If it comes to it.

346
00:22:22.007 --> 00:22:23.925
Civilian interference
with a police investigation

347
00:22:24.009 --> 00:22:25.560
poses many a problem
in a court of law.

348
00:22:25.584 --> 00:22:27.209
Okay. listen to me. Judy.

349
00:22:27.555 --> 00:22:29.764
I don't mind that you're working
with my husband

350
00:22:29.849 --> 00:22:33.017
or that you even bake him
those little treats as you do.

351
00:22:33.102 --> 00:22:34.996
But if you're gonna start
acting like him.

352
00:22:35.010 --> 00:22:37.011
you ought to put a mustache on
'cause you sound ridiculous.

353
00:22:37.256 --> 00:22:38.631
- Gale!
- Judy!

354
00:22:38.716 --> 00:22:40.227
Gale!

355
00:22:40.751 --> 00:22:42.751
Deputy. Gale.

356
00:22:43.112 --> 00:22:45.238
Please.

357
00:22:45.322 --> 00:22:47.574
Uh. Sidney.
if you don't mind givin' us a minute.

358
00:22:47.658 --> 00:22:49.701
- Sid.
- Hi. Gale.

359
00:22:49.785 --> 00:22:53.037
Dewey. would you please explain
to Betty Crocker

360
00:22:53.122 --> 00:22:55.248
that I have every right to be here?

361
00:22:55.332 --> 00:22:58.960
If there's been another murder
in Woodsboro. obviously... what?

362
00:22:59.044 --> 00:23:01.588
That is not public information!

363
00:23:01.672 --> 00:23:04.507
- It is all over the Internet. Dewey!
- It is?

364
00:23:04.592 --> 00:23:07.552
Yes! The whole world knows
about it before me!

365
00:23:07.636 --> 00:23:10.346
She wants to be a part
of the investigation. Sheriff.

366
00:23:10.431 --> 00:23:12.265
Hang on.

367
00:23:12.349 --> 00:23:18.021
Um. are you familiar with the phrase.
"I wrote the book on this"?

368
00:23:21.150 --> 00:23:24.944
Gale. with all due respect.
I don't see how that pertains to...

369
00:23:25.029 --> 00:23:27.822
Because I wrote the book on this!

370
00:23:27.907 --> 00:23:31.492
"The Woodsboro Murders"
by Gale Weathers?

371
00:23:31.577 --> 00:23:34.037
But you're not a reporter anymore.
Gale.

372
00:23:34.121 --> 00:23:35.538
- Whoa. whoa. whoa. whoa.
- And even if you were...

373
00:23:35.623 --> 00:23:37.707
Don't treat me like I'm the media.

374
00:23:37.791 --> 00:23:42.045
I helped solve these things
three times. remember?

375
00:23:42.129 --> 00:23:43.922
You and me. Together.

376
00:23:44.006 --> 00:23:46.799
But I'm the Sheriff now. Gale.

377
00:23:47.584 --> 00:23:49.219
Right?

378
00:23:50.304 --> 00:23:52.639
What. you're not gonna let me
help you with this?

379
00:23:52.723 --> 00:23:55.642
I can't.

380
00:23:55.726 --> 00:23:58.019
All right.
then I'm going rogue.

381
00:23:58.103 --> 00:24:00.563
This is what I'm good at. Dewey.

382
00:24:00.648 --> 00:24:04.484
This is what I know how to do.

383
00:24:08.739 --> 00:24:11.032
Your lemon squares taste like ass.

384
00:24:13.077 --> 00:24:16.037
They don't.
They really don't.

385
00:24:16.121 --> 00:24:17.246
Thank you. sir.

386
00:24:17.331 --> 00:24:19.332
- Sheriff.
- Yeah?

387
00:24:19.416 --> 00:24:21.084
We've got a couple
high school kids in here.

388
00:24:21.168 --> 00:24:24.170
Two of 'em. they say they got
threatening phone calls this morning

389
00:24:24.254 --> 00:24:25.922
from the victims' phones.

390
00:24:26.006 --> 00:24:29.467
Names are Olivia Morris
and Jill Roberts.

391
00:24:29.551 --> 00:24:32.762
That's Sid's cousin. Damn.

392
00:24:32.846 --> 00:24:35.181
Right in here. Sheriff.

393
00:24:35.265 --> 00:24:37.308
- Hey. Jill.
- Sidney.

394
00:24:37.393 --> 00:24:39.602
- Hi.
- Hi.

395
00:24:39.687 --> 00:24:42.105
It's nice to see you
even under the circumstances.

396
00:24:42.189 --> 00:24:44.190
You okay?

397
00:24:44.274 --> 00:24:46.818
- Yeah.
- So two of you got phone calls?

398
00:24:46.902 --> 00:24:50.446
Yeah. us two.
"What's your favorite scary movie?"

399
00:24:50.531 --> 00:24:53.616
It was the killer's voice.
From "Stab."

400
00:24:53.701 --> 00:24:56.327
Or. I mean. you know.
from your life.

401
00:24:56.412 --> 00:24:58.871
I'm Kirby. by the way.
I'm their friend.

402
00:24:59.656 --> 00:25:01.274
And the killer didn't call you?

403
00:25:01.458 --> 00:25:05.461
No.
Is... is that a bad thing?

404
00:25:05.546 --> 00:25:07.588
Does that mean that I'm not gonna
live as long as these two?

405
00:25:07.673 --> 00:25:08.798
No.

406
00:25:08.882 --> 00:25:10.008
Maybe.

407
00:25:10.092 --> 00:25:13.678
Of course not.
Just. uh. just be careful.

408
00:25:13.762 --> 00:25:16.973
Oh. my God. did you hear that?
I'm gonna be next!

409
00:25:17.057 --> 00:25:19.142
Dewey. I shouldn't be here.
I should leave town.

410
00:25:19.226 --> 00:25:21.310
I'm afraid that's not
really possible. Sidney.

411
00:25:21.395 --> 00:25:26.858
Look. nobody thinks you're involved.
but everyone's a suspect. I'm sorry.

412
00:25:26.942 --> 00:25:29.819
And there was evidence in your car.
connecting the killer to you.

413
00:25:29.903 --> 00:25:31.446
You may be a material witness.

414
00:25:33.741 --> 00:25:38.286
So. look. you'll have. uh.
24-hour police surveillance.

415
00:25:38.370 --> 00:25:40.322
That's comforting.

416
00:25:41.707 --> 00:25:43.458
This is Rebecca.

417
00:25:43.542 --> 00:25:47.754
Oh. my fucking God. Henry!
Yes! It's true.

418
00:25:47.838 --> 00:25:51.174
Two girls butchered.
Payday.

419
00:25:51.258 --> 00:25:54.969
I was so not feeling Woodsboro.
I was like. lame PR move. right?

420
00:25:55.054 --> 00:25:59.474
Well. fuck me wow.
Best idea ever.

421
00:25:59.558 --> 00:26:01.560
Henry. I'll call you back.

422
00:26:02.644 --> 00:26:04.687
Excuse me I have to geek out.

423
00:26:04.772 --> 00:26:06.272
I didn't get a chance
to say something earlier.

424
00:26:06.356 --> 00:26:07.940
but it's such an honor to meet you.

425
00:26:08.025 --> 00:26:10.401
- Thank you. Hi.
- Rebecca Walters.

426
00:26:10.486 --> 00:26:13.362
When I was a kid. it was all about
"Top Story with Gale Weathers."

427
00:26:13.447 --> 00:26:16.783
- You were my '90s.
- Well. it's Gale Riley now.

428
00:26:16.867 --> 00:26:18.534
You gave it all up for love.
I know that.

429
00:26:18.619 --> 00:26:19.994
How long have you
and Dewey been married?

430
00:26:20.079 --> 00:26:21.829
Ten years.

431
00:26:21.914 --> 00:26:24.165
Just like your characters
in "Stab 3." Wow.

432
00:26:24.249 --> 00:26:26.000
Wow.

433
00:26:26.085 --> 00:26:28.252
Oh. I didn't mean bad wow.

434
00:26:28.337 --> 00:26:30.379
It just. it always seemed like more
of a movie romance than a real one

435
00:26:30.464 --> 00:26:33.591
because it was a movie and in real life
you two would never be...

436
00:26:33.675 --> 00:26:37.261
Ooh. dug a hole.
Climbing out here.

437
00:26:37.346 --> 00:26:41.024
So anyway kudos on being brave enough
to drop off the professional map.

438
00:26:41.108 --> 00:26:43.985
Any plans on revitalizing
your tarnished brand?

439
00:26:44.269 --> 00:26:45.804
Listen. in about two seconds.

440
00:26:45.828 --> 00:26:49.447
I'm gonna revitalize your face
with my tarnished brand.

441
00:26:50.692 --> 00:26:53.653
I still got it.

442
00:26:53.737 --> 00:26:55.613
Testy.

443
00:27:03.872 --> 00:27:06.040
She's so pretty.

444
00:27:06.125 --> 00:27:08.501
When you think about what she survived.
she must have scars everywhere.

445
00:27:10.879 --> 00:27:15.049
Her mom was my sister.
I have scars. too.

446
00:27:15.134 --> 00:27:17.844
No one ever asks me
about my scars.

447
00:27:17.928 --> 00:27:21.722
- I'm sorry. Mrs. Roberts.
- She means knife scars. Mom.

448
00:27:23.400 --> 00:27:26.036
Well... fine.

449
00:27:27.521 --> 00:27:29.856
How are you?

450
00:27:29.940 --> 00:27:32.108
How's Gale?

451
00:27:32.192 --> 00:27:35.236
Uh. I'm all right.

452
00:27:35.320 --> 00:27:39.282
But Gale. it's been hard on her.

453
00:27:39.366 --> 00:27:42.743
Small town...
small-town husband.

454
00:27:42.828 --> 00:27:45.997
Not much to write about.

455
00:27:47.141 --> 00:27:49.894
You two okay?

456
00:27:49.918 --> 00:27:52.920
Well. I read somewhere once.

457
00:27:53.005 --> 00:27:56.215
"Just when you think
things can't get any worse.

458
00:27:56.300 --> 00:27:57.884
"sometimes they don't.

459
00:27:57.968 --> 00:28:00.761
Sometimes they get better."

460
00:28:00.846 --> 00:28:04.056
"Out of Darkness" by Sidney Prescott.
page 220.

461
00:28:13.315 --> 00:28:15.309
Gotta get going.

462
00:28:21.033 --> 00:28:24.577
It's nice to see you. Dewey.
Been through a lot together.

463
00:28:24.661 --> 00:28:27.288
And we'll get through this. too.
Okay?

464
00:28:27.372 --> 00:28:29.248
Lock up.

465
00:28:48.852 --> 00:28:50.228
Be cool.

466
00:28:50.312 --> 00:28:52.980
It's okay. It's just me.
Relax. relax. It's just me.

467
00:28:53.065 --> 00:28:55.650
What the hell are you doing here?
There are cops right out front.

468
00:28:55.734 --> 00:28:58.236
No match for the ninja. baby.

469
00:29:00.197 --> 00:29:03.616
Anyway. what are you doing in
the house with Sidney Prescott?

470
00:29:03.700 --> 00:29:06.077
I mean. that's like being on "Top Chef"
with Jeffrey Dahmer.

471
00:29:06.161 --> 00:29:08.704
Can you please get away
from the window?

472
00:29:08.789 --> 00:29:12.208
Y... You have no right to be in here.
Not anymore.

473
00:29:12.292 --> 00:29:13.876
Hang on.

474
00:29:13.961 --> 00:29:17.004
I heard you got a phone call
from the killer.

475
00:29:17.089 --> 00:29:19.966
- Is that true?
- What do you care?

476
00:29:20.050 --> 00:29:23.052
Don't you think you'd be
a lot safer with me around?

477
00:29:23.136 --> 00:29:25.346
I don't trust you Trevor.

478
00:29:25.430 --> 00:29:26.722
Hey.

479
00:29:26.807 --> 00:29:30.309
Then I'm just gonna have
to make sure that you do. all right?

480
00:29:33.146 --> 00:29:34.855
Oh. sorry. I didn't...

481
00:29:34.940 --> 00:29:37.608
No. he's just leaving.
It's... it's my ex.

482
00:29:37.693 --> 00:29:38.901
Oh.

483
00:29:38.986 --> 00:29:41.779
Yeah.
Her one and only.

484
00:29:41.863 --> 00:29:44.031
- Hi.
- Hi.

485
00:29:44.116 --> 00:29:46.826
It's cool to meet you... officially.

486
00:29:46.910 --> 00:29:51.998
I keep meaning to pick up a copy
of your book. but...

487
00:29:52.082 --> 00:29:54.583
You're smaller in person.

488
00:30:01.925 --> 00:30:03.134
What?

489
00:30:03.218 --> 00:30:08.055
Nothing. You just. uh...
you remind me of. uh... me.

490
00:30:09.801 --> 00:30:11.828
Lock your window. okay?

491
00:30:11.852 --> 00:30:13.769
Yeah. Good night.

492
00:30:13.854 --> 00:30:16.147
'Night.

493
00:30:17.292 --> 00:30:18.960
Sorry about that.

494
00:30:20.245 --> 00:30:23.006
Just makin' my rounds
before takin' off.

495
00:30:23.030 --> 00:30:25.656
Great. Thanks.

496
00:30:27.201 --> 00:30:29.804
Y... You don't remember me.
do ya?

497
00:30:29.828 --> 00:30:31.245
Sorry?

498
00:30:31.330 --> 00:30:35.041
We went to high school together.
Judy Hicks?

499
00:30:35.125 --> 00:30:39.253
We had the same homeroom
and Drama Club. too.

500
00:30:39.338 --> 00:30:43.424
We were in "Peter Pan" together.
I played a Lost Boy.

501
00:30:43.508 --> 00:30:47.511
You were... Tiger Lily.

502
00:30:49.139 --> 00:30:52.600
I'm sorry.
that was a long time ago.

503
00:30:53.145 --> 00:30:55.163
It's okay.

504
00:30:55.187 --> 00:30:59.690
You had a lot of stuff goin'
on back then.

505
00:31:00.275 --> 00:31:03.394
Well. it's nice to see you again. Judy.

506
00:31:03.578 --> 00:31:04.662
You too.

507
00:31:11.644 --> 00:31:13.535
Everything okay upstairs?

508
00:31:13.538 --> 00:31:15.875
You're supposed to be out front.
Perkins.

509
00:31:24.591 --> 00:31:27.218
What's a 4-letter word
for "courage"?

510
00:31:29.554 --> 00:31:30.763
"guts."

511
00:31:36.144 --> 00:31:38.396
That's Olivia Morris.
She lives next door.

512
00:31:38.480 --> 00:31:40.440
She's on the list.

513
00:31:41.525 --> 00:31:43.859
She can live next door to me.

514
00:31:43.944 --> 00:31:46.612
Now. seriously. uh...
uh. Mary.

515
00:31:46.696 --> 00:31:48.697
I'm warning you. okay.
I'm gonna have to get physical.

516
00:31:48.782 --> 00:31:51.117
I mean it. This is it!

517
00:31:51.201 --> 00:31:52.827
Just fuck off!

518
00:32:02.991 --> 00:32:04.376
Hello?

519
00:32:04.400 --> 00:32:05.817
What are you guys up to?

520
00:32:05.841 --> 00:32:07.883
Oh.
we're watching "Shaun of the Dead."

521
00:32:07.968 --> 00:32:10.553
You know there are two zombies
sitting outside the house in a car?

522
00:32:10.637 --> 00:32:13.722
Yup. They're cops.
You wanna come up?

523
00:32:13.807 --> 00:32:15.015
The Angel of Death leave?

524
00:32:15.100 --> 00:32:17.268
No. she's in the guest room.

525
00:32:17.352 --> 00:32:20.396
Forget it.
Next door's close enough.

526
00:32:20.480 --> 00:32:23.983
- Your mom home?
- She's at her boyfriend's.

527
00:32:24.067 --> 00:32:25.860
It's creepy around here tonight.

528
00:32:25.944 --> 00:32:28.237
Well. the zombies
are still in their car.

529
00:32:28.321 --> 00:32:31.407
So you should be all right.

530
00:32:31.491 --> 00:32:33.951
- Call me tomorrow. okay?
- All right.

531
00:32:34.035 --> 00:32:37.246
- She didn't wanna come up?
- She fears the Reaper.

532
00:32:37.730 --> 00:32:39.832
Watch this.

533
00:32:48.067 --> 00:32:49.485
Speaking.

534
00:32:49.509 --> 00:32:53.637
What's your favorite
scary movie. Olivia?

535
00:32:53.722 --> 00:32:56.140
That's the worst imitation
I've ever heard. Jill.

536
00:32:56.224 --> 00:32:58.476
Speaking of "Stab." you heard
where the Stab-a-Thon's gonna be yet?

537
00:32:58.560 --> 00:33:00.811
No. and it doesn't matter to me anyways.

538
00:33:00.896 --> 00:33:02.897
My mom doesn't let me go.

539
00:33:04.041 --> 00:33:05.543
It's Trevor.

540
00:33:05.567 --> 00:33:09.570
- I'll handle this.
- Trevor's calling. Again.

541
00:33:09.654 --> 00:33:12.907
- What do you want?
- I wanna talk to Jill.

542
00:33:12.991 --> 00:33:15.326
Uh. no. it's Kirby.
Sorry. Trevor.

543
00:33:15.410 --> 00:33:18.579
Jill is screening her calls
from all past relationships.

544
00:33:18.663 --> 00:33:19.747
What's going on over there?

545
00:33:19.831 --> 00:33:21.999
Hang on a sec.
What is he saying?

546
00:33:22.083 --> 00:33:23.876
I'm not Trevor.

547
00:33:23.960 --> 00:33:27.087
Wh... what?
I can barely hear you. Trevor.

548
00:33:27.172 --> 00:33:29.632
This isn't Trevor.

549
00:33:29.716 --> 00:33:31.050
Oh. a... all right.

550
00:33:31.134 --> 00:33:34.345
Well. then. why do you have his phone.
whoever this is?

551
00:33:34.429 --> 00:33:36.680
He's trying to do Ghostface.

552
00:33:36.765 --> 00:33:39.141
He's being weird.

553
00:33:39.226 --> 00:33:40.893
I wanna talk to Jill.

554
00:33:40.977 --> 00:33:43.729
Okay. well.
she doesn't wanna talk to you.

555
00:33:43.813 --> 00:33:45.814
Come on. Mr. Ghostface.
whisper to me.

556
00:33:45.899 --> 00:33:49.068
Aren't you supposed
to ask me a question?

557
00:33:49.152 --> 00:33:51.820
All right.
How's the movie?

558
00:33:51.905 --> 00:33:53.155
What movie?

559
00:33:53.240 --> 00:33:55.492
"Shaun of the Dead."

560
00:33:56.576 --> 00:33:58.118
How did you know that?

561
00:33:58.203 --> 00:34:01.705
Because I'm standing
in the closet.

562
00:34:01.790 --> 00:34:03.541
Stop. You are not.

563
00:34:03.625 --> 00:34:06.085
- What's going on?
- Trevor's being weird.

564
00:34:06.169 --> 00:34:08.254
- I mean. if it is him. I don't know.
- What?

565
00:34:08.338 --> 00:34:10.256
This is not fucking Trevor!

566
00:34:10.340 --> 00:34:12.299
Well then.
who the fuck are you?

567
00:34:12.384 --> 00:34:14.468
Open the closet door.

568
00:34:17.180 --> 00:34:19.348
You do know there are cops
all over this house?

569
00:34:19.432 --> 00:34:23.435
I think I'd have just enough time
to slice someone open.

570
00:34:23.520 --> 00:34:27.690
I-I'll talk to him.

571
00:34:27.774 --> 00:34:30.067
What's going on
over there. you guys?

572
00:34:30.151 --> 00:34:33.195
S... Sorry.
I... I don't know. Kirby.

573
00:34:33.280 --> 00:34:34.738
Kirby.

574
00:34:34.823 --> 00:34:36.323
Come on. do it.

575
00:34:36.408 --> 00:34:38.450
There is no way you're in there.

576
00:34:38.535 --> 00:34:41.036
See for yourself.

577
00:34:41.121 --> 00:34:42.830
Kirby?

578
00:34:42.914 --> 00:34:46.250
Kirby. come on. Talk to me.
This isn't funny.

579
00:34:46.334 --> 00:34:47.960
Kirby!

580
00:34:54.526 --> 00:34:56.611
Liar. I'm over this.

581
00:34:56.695 --> 00:34:59.197
I never said I was in your closet.

582
00:35:04.996 --> 00:35:07.582
Oh. my God. Olivia!

583
00:35:08.667 --> 00:35:11.294
Oh. my God. help!

584
00:35:22.412 --> 00:35:23.662
No! Help!

585
00:35:38.470 --> 00:35:40.680
- Hoss!
- Somebody help!

586
00:35:40.691 --> 00:35:42.692
Perkins!

587
00:35:43.350 --> 00:35:44.944
Shit!

588
00:35:46.728 --> 00:35:49.813
Help! Help!

589
00:36:40.918 --> 00:36:41.918
What?

590
00:36:41.922 --> 00:36:45.024
Welcome home. Sidney.
Preview of coming events.

591
00:36:45.286 --> 00:36:47.413
Why don't you come for me?
You got the balls for that?

592
00:36:47.497 --> 00:36:50.040
Oh. poor Sidney.
You think this is all about you.

593
00:36:50.125 --> 00:36:53.377
- You think you're still the star.
- This isn't a fucking movie!

594
00:36:53.461 --> 00:36:55.462
- It will be.
- These are innocent people.

595
00:36:55.465 --> 00:36:56.715
Spare me the lecture.

596
00:36:56.881 --> 00:36:59.633
You've done very well
by all this bloodshed. haven't you?

597
00:36:59.718 --> 00:37:01.885
Well. how about
the town you left behind?

598
00:37:01.970 --> 00:37:03.721
I've got plans for you.

599
00:37:03.805 --> 00:37:06.306
I'm gonna slit your eyelids in half
so you don't blink

600
00:37:06.391 --> 00:37:08.559
when I stab you in the face.

601
00:37:08.643 --> 00:37:12.354
You'll die when I want you to. Sidney.
Not a moment before.

602
00:37:12.439 --> 00:37:15.482
Until then...
you're going to suffer.

603
00:37:16.943 --> 00:37:18.986
- Sidney?!
- Jill?

604
00:37:19.070 --> 00:37:22.030
- Stay right there!
- Is she...

605
00:37:22.115 --> 00:37:24.241
Do not look. Okay?

606
00:37:24.325 --> 00:37:26.910
She said
you were the Angel of Death.

607
00:37:26.995 --> 00:37:28.996
Look out!

608
00:37:50.101 --> 00:37:53.112
- What's going on in here?
- He's in here.

609
00:37:53.196 --> 00:37:55.116
Where is he?

610
00:37:57.400 --> 00:38:00.862
- He was.
- We'll check out back.

611
00:38:01.186 --> 00:38:04.105
- Jill?
- Don't.

612
00:38:13.625 --> 00:38:16.043
What happened?

613
00:38:16.127 --> 00:38:19.213
Oh. my God. Jill.

614
00:38:19.297 --> 00:38:24.635
Jesus! I'm here. Come on.
Let's go. Let's go. All right?

615
00:38:25.980 --> 00:38:27.490
Jill?

616
00:38:27.514 --> 00:38:29.723
Oh. my God.
Are you okay?

617
00:38:29.808 --> 00:38:32.851
- Here. keep pressure on it.
- There's nobody back there.

618
00:38:33.797 --> 00:38:35.840
- Hoss. call it in.
- Right.

619
00:38:36.064 --> 00:38:40.442
Hey.
Are you okay?

620
00:38:40.527 --> 00:38:42.319
You should look upstairs.

621
00:38:53.664 --> 00:38:57.084
Let's get the coroner's van
brought around. please.

622
00:39:01.208 --> 00:39:03.182
I thought this was over!

623
00:39:06.189 --> 00:39:08.399
It's all your fault. Sidney!

624
00:39:08.483 --> 00:39:10.693
You're just like your mother!

625
00:39:10.977 --> 00:39:12.353
- Hoss. clear these people out.
- Right.

626
00:39:16.104 --> 00:39:19.690
I'm sorry about what I said.

627
00:39:19.774 --> 00:39:22.109
Do you wanna go get that looked at?

628
00:39:22.193 --> 00:39:25.529
Yeah.

629
00:39:25.613 --> 00:39:27.322
What the hell happened?

630
00:39:27.407 --> 00:39:31.076
Okay. I saw him go into that yard
two houses down right before...

631
00:39:31.160 --> 00:39:33.453
Yeah. and I circled around
to cut him off.

632
00:39:33.538 --> 00:39:34.705
And?

633
00:39:34.789 --> 00:39:37.207
And I met Hoss coming
from the other direction.

634
00:39:37.292 --> 00:39:40.168
He must've circled back around somehow.
He's like a ghost.

635
00:39:40.953 --> 00:39:44.414
- Chief. we're sorry.
- We feel terrible.

636
00:39:44.498 --> 00:39:47.500
All right.
Get outta here.

637
00:40:00.782 --> 00:40:04.618
This is "Hall Pass" with Robbie Mercer.
webcasting live in our darkest hour.

638
00:40:04.703 --> 00:40:07.579
What began as a day of remembrance
has ended with serial murder.

639
00:40:07.864 --> 00:40:12.034
Olivia Morris. who officially
will never go out with me. is dead.

640
00:40:12.118 --> 00:40:14.369
So is Jenny Randall
and Marnie Cooper.

641
00:40:14.454 --> 00:40:18.206
Our local legacy. the "Stab" movies.
is coming to life.

642
00:40:18.291 --> 00:40:21.209
Excuse me.
Are you recording with that thing?

643
00:40:21.294 --> 00:40:24.046
Live video-blog upload.
He's webcasting right now.

644
00:40:24.130 --> 00:40:26.465
Oh. Mind turning it off
for a little old-school off the record?

645
00:40:26.549 --> 00:40:28.759
Can't.
Owe it to my audience.

646
00:40:28.843 --> 00:40:30.677
Turn that fucking thing off.

647
00:40:30.762 --> 00:40:32.220
Okay.

648
00:40:32.865 --> 00:40:37.369
So. you two are the boys that run
the movie club at Woodsboro High. huh?

649
00:40:37.393 --> 00:40:40.520
Charlie runs it.
I'm just V.P. In case he takes a bullet.

650
00:40:40.605 --> 00:40:42.064
It's called Cinema Club.

651
00:40:42.148 --> 00:40:47.027
So you must have a very unique insight
into the movie buffs at your school.

652
00:40:47.111 --> 00:40:48.862
Maybe.

653
00:40:48.947 --> 00:40:52.991
What if we could catch the killer
by working together?

654
00:40:53.076 --> 00:40:55.619
Two generations
of cutting-edge journalists

655
00:40:55.703 --> 00:40:58.830
intertwining our passions for media?

656
00:40:58.915 --> 00:41:01.041
What would you say?

657
00:41:01.125 --> 00:41:02.376
I love you.

658
00:41:02.460 --> 00:41:04.002
Very good.

659
00:41:04.087 --> 00:41:08.048
Now you give me your expertise
on the gore geek scene at Woodsboro High

660
00:41:08.132 --> 00:41:10.801
and maybe
I give you something in return.

661
00:41:10.885 --> 00:41:14.221
Say. a celebrity visit
to your Cinema Club?

662
00:41:14.305 --> 00:41:16.974
By me.

663
00:41:17.058 --> 00:41:21.019
What about Sidney?

664
00:41:21.104 --> 00:41:24.022
Yeah. you know her. right?
I mean. you're friends with her?

665
00:41:24.107 --> 00:41:26.942
No offense. but that'd be a big deal
for Cinema Club.

666
00:41:27.026 --> 00:41:29.820
A visit from Sidney Prescott?
I mean. she's the star.

667
00:41:29.904 --> 00:41:34.324
Yes. she's
Daniel Radcliffe to my J.K. Rowling.

668
00:41:34.409 --> 00:41:36.952
Well. without the book sales
and the box office.

669
00:41:37.297 --> 00:41:39.590
Whatever.

670
00:41:41.575 --> 00:41:43.135
There's no broken bones.

671
00:41:43.159 --> 00:41:46.119
I think you'll be fine.
Just take a couple days off.

672
00:41:49.468 --> 00:41:51.694
So. Sidney. ooh. ow.

673
00:41:51.718 --> 00:41:53.635
Anyway. long story short.

674
00:41:53.720 --> 00:41:57.014
Random wants to lock you in
to three more books now.

675
00:41:57.098 --> 00:42:00.600
See the blank line in your contract?
You can name your price.

676
00:42:00.685 --> 00:42:02.686
And as soon as you're clear
in this investigation.

677
00:42:02.770 --> 00:42:04.296
we're on the next plane to New York.

678
00:42:04.301 --> 00:42:06.845
I booked "Today." "The View."
"Nancy Grace." "MTV News"...

679
00:42:07.108 --> 00:42:09.026
Excuse me.
Can I ask you a question?

680
00:42:10.210 --> 00:42:12.295
Did you read my book?

681
00:42:13.480 --> 00:42:15.398
Thought I'd wait for the movie.

682
00:42:15.683 --> 00:42:17.200
Book tour's over.

683
00:42:17.285 --> 00:42:19.036
Sidney.

684
00:42:19.120 --> 00:42:21.538
Accept your situation.

685
00:42:21.622 --> 00:42:23.790
You're a victim. For life.

686
00:42:23.875 --> 00:42:27.002
So embrace it. use it.

687
00:42:27.086 --> 00:42:29.504
I know
you care about your readers.

688
00:42:29.589 --> 00:42:31.631
All those little downtrodden fucks
that just need a light

689
00:42:31.716 --> 00:42:33.925
at the end of their tunnel
so they don't jump off a bridge.

690
00:42:34.010 --> 00:42:35.469
And a lucky break like this?

691
00:42:35.553 --> 00:42:38.388
I'm talkin' 100% increase in sales.
minimum.

692
00:42:38.473 --> 00:42:40.807
That's maybe a million more people
get your message.

693
00:42:40.892 --> 00:42:43.685
and you get a ton more checks.
win-win.

694
00:42:45.831 --> 00:42:47.583
I won't be needing you anymore.

695
00:42:47.607 --> 00:42:49.524
- Sidney.
- You're fired.

696
00:42:49.609 --> 00:42:51.818
- Fired?
- Fired.

697
00:42:52.903 --> 00:42:54.480
Fine.

698
00:43:16.518 --> 00:43:19.395
"Have you even read my book.
Rebecca?"

699
00:43:31.859 --> 00:43:34.194
The problem with Sidney
is that she never gets laid.

700
00:43:34.278 --> 00:43:37.489
Or even a little shit-faced
once in a while.

701
00:43:37.573 --> 00:43:39.658
She'll call me tonight and apologize.

702
00:43:39.742 --> 00:43:42.202
Just watch.

703
00:43:48.000 --> 00:43:49.876
She'll come around.

704
00:43:49.961 --> 00:43:54.548
Gotta just give her time.
and Sidney will come around.

705
00:43:56.634 --> 00:43:58.510
Where did I?

706
00:44:06.963 --> 00:44:08.497
This is Rebecca.

707
00:44:08.499 --> 00:44:10.542
Sidney Prescott. please.

708
00:44:10.648 --> 00:44:12.843
I'm handling Miss Prescott's calls
and appearances.

709
00:44:12.847 --> 00:44:16.349
- May I take a message?
- You are the message.

710
00:44:20.091 --> 00:44:23.177
- Are you writing this down?
- Yes. I am.

711
00:44:23.461 --> 00:44:25.837
It's kind of hard to hear you.
I'm in the hospital with Sidney.

712
00:44:26.122 --> 00:44:28.206
If you could just hang on one second.

713
00:44:28.291 --> 00:44:31.626
I've got time.
It's you that doesn't.

714
00:44:39.811 --> 00:44:40.904
You know. Rebecca.

715
00:44:40.910 --> 00:44:43.871
it doesn't sound to me
like you're in the hospital.

716
00:44:43.973 --> 00:44:47.142
Sounds like you're in a parking garage.

717
00:44:47.226 --> 00:44:50.854
A dark and deserted parking garage.

718
00:44:52.232 --> 00:44:55.526
But if you want to be in the hospital.
I'd be happy to put you there.

719
00:44:56.010 --> 00:44:57.969
In the morgue!

720
00:45:19.124 --> 00:45:20.833
No.

721
00:45:44.675 --> 00:45:46.910
Help! Help!

722
00:45:46.995 --> 00:45:48.787
Help me!

723
00:45:48.872 --> 00:45:50.581
Help!

724
00:46:03.719 --> 00:46:06.304
Cut and run.
you fucking bastard.

725
00:47:14.999 --> 00:47:17.417
This is an ongoing investigation.

726
00:47:18.062 --> 00:47:21.657
Rest assured.
we're pursuing a number of leads.

727
00:47:21.881 --> 00:47:24.215
The less I say about that.
the better.

728
00:47:24.300 --> 00:47:28.178
- So I'm taking questions.
- Sheriff! Sheriff!

729
00:47:28.262 --> 00:47:30.013
- Dewey!
- Gale?

730
00:47:30.097 --> 00:47:32.182
Any comment on the fact
that these killings

731
00:47:32.266 --> 00:47:35.685
seem to resemble the pattern
of the original Woodsboro Murders?

732
00:47:35.770 --> 00:47:37.771
Hon? Later.

733
00:47:37.855 --> 00:47:39.731
What was that. Sheriff?

734
00:47:39.815 --> 00:47:43.943
As I was saying. uh.
my officers are hard at work.

735
00:47:44.028 --> 00:47:47.655
and we just want the community
to know that we are very close

736
00:47:47.740 --> 00:47:50.200
to bringing this whole situation
under control...

737
00:47:54.330 --> 00:47:57.415
Oh. shit!

738
00:47:57.500 --> 00:48:00.668
Someone. get up to the top
of the structure! Go. go!

739
00:48:00.753 --> 00:48:03.797
- Everyone back! Stay back!
- All right. nobody move!

740
00:48:03.881 --> 00:48:05.715
Listen.
I want a man on each stairwell!

741
00:48:08.552 --> 00:48:11.471
- You see anybody?
- Nobody up here.

742
00:48:11.555 --> 00:48:13.932
There's nobody up there.
Sheriff!

743
00:48:14.776 --> 00:48:17.287
It's all under control.
huh. Sheriff?

744
00:48:17.311 --> 00:48:19.437
What am I supposed to say?

745
00:48:19.522 --> 00:48:21.731
Listen.
I may not be wearing a uniform.

746
00:48:21.755 --> 00:48:24.048
but I happen to have a lead.
and you don't.

747
00:48:25.093 --> 00:48:28.438
So let me know when
you're back on Team Gale.

748
00:48:29.722 --> 00:48:32.226
Move it. amateurs!

749
00:48:32.910 --> 00:48:34.828
And remember. students.

750
00:48:34.912 --> 00:48:38.081
tonight's town curfew is 9:00.

751
00:48:38.165 --> 00:48:42.085
You should be home with your doors
locked at 9:00.

752
00:48:42.169 --> 00:48:44.421
Okay. Cinema Club.
We are now in session.

753
00:48:44.505 --> 00:48:47.465
Welcome.
Tell you a little bit about ourselves.

754
00:48:47.550 --> 00:48:50.385
We are a sanctioned
after-school activity.

755
00:48:50.469 --> 00:48:54.514
one rung below the Glee Club.
two above Nintendo Wii Fit.

756
00:48:54.598 --> 00:48:58.810
And let me just say
to our guest. Sidney Prescott.

757
00:48:58.894 --> 00:49:00.395
it's an honor.

758
00:49:02.982 --> 00:49:05.692
Beyond Jamie Lee Curtis.
forget Linda Blair.

759
00:49:05.776 --> 00:49:07.986
I mean. this is the ultimate.

760
00:49:08.070 --> 00:49:09.696
Thanks. I guess.

761
00:49:09.780 --> 00:49:12.282
Um this.
you film your entire

762
00:49:12.366 --> 00:49:14.534
high school experience and.
what. post it on the net?

763
00:49:14.618 --> 00:49:16.494
Everybody'll be doing it someday. Sid.

764
00:49:16.579 --> 00:49:19.330
It's kind of the one component
the killer is missing.

765
00:49:19.415 --> 00:49:21.332
Wait.
What do you mean?

766
00:49:21.417 --> 00:49:23.418
Well. if you wanna be
the new version.

767
00:49:23.502 --> 00:49:25.753
the killer
should be filming the murders.

768
00:49:25.838 --> 00:49:28.882
It's like the natural next step
in a psycho slasher innovation.

769
00:49:28.966 --> 00:49:31.468
I mean. you film 'em all real-time.
and then before you get caught.

770
00:49:31.552 --> 00:49:34.846
- you upload 'em into cyberspace.
- Making your art as immortal as you.

771
00:49:35.830 --> 00:49:37.874
- Not to implicate him.
- Not to implicate me.

772
00:49:37.898 --> 00:49:39.816
So who do you think
is behind the murders?

773
00:49:41.121 --> 00:49:43.874
Well. it's a "Stab" fanatic clearly.

774
00:49:43.898 --> 00:49:46.649
Working on less of a shriekquel and...
and more of a scream-make.

775
00:49:46.734 --> 00:49:49.194
- Copyrighted terms. by the way.
- 'Cause all there are now are remakes.

776
00:49:49.278 --> 00:49:51.738
Only horror the studios green-light.
I mean

777
00:49:51.822 --> 00:49:52.989
There are still rules.

778
00:49:53.073 --> 00:49:56.201
But the rules have changed.
The unexpected is the new cliché.

779
00:49:56.285 --> 00:49:59.162
Yeah. you gotta have an opening sequence
that blows the doors off.

780
00:49:59.246 --> 00:50:01.331
dial up some flashy
music-video direction.

781
00:50:01.415 --> 00:50:03.124
and the kills gotta be
way more extreme.

782
00:50:03.209 --> 00:50:06.252
Modern audiences get savvy
to the rules of the originals.

783
00:50:06.337 --> 00:50:08.171
So the reversals
become the new standard.

784
00:50:08.255 --> 00:50:11.716
In fact. the only surefire way
to survive a modern horror movie?

785
00:50:11.800 --> 00:50:14.387
You pretty much have to be gay.

786
00:50:16.472 --> 00:50:20.433
So why are you so sure that the killer's
working by the rules of a horror remake?

787
00:50:20.518 --> 00:50:22.810
Well. the original "Stab" structure
is pretty apparent.

788
00:50:22.895 --> 00:50:25.355
Yeah. two kids killed in a house
when their parents are away?

789
00:50:25.439 --> 00:50:28.149
And then the school's hot chick
savaged beyond recognition.

790
00:50:28.234 --> 00:50:30.568
- We all know where it goes from there.
- A party.

791
00:50:30.653 --> 00:50:33.655
Exactly. A party.

792
00:50:33.739 --> 00:50:35.865
Guaranteed third-act
main cast bloodbath.

793
00:50:35.950 --> 00:50:37.825
Fingers crossed
on some nudity for a change.

794
00:50:40.079 --> 00:50:42.580
Okay. so do you know of a party
that's happening tonight?

795
00:50:42.665 --> 00:50:46.125
Well. there's Stab-a-Thon.

796
00:50:46.210 --> 00:50:48.294
Stab-a-Thon?

797
00:50:48.379 --> 00:50:50.713
Uh. it's a movie marathon.
All seven "Stabs" back-to-back.

798
00:50:50.798 --> 00:50:53.466
- We do it every year.
- And it's tonight?

799
00:50:54.011 --> 00:50:55.570
There's a killer out there

800
00:50:55.574 --> 00:50:57.742
patterning his murders
after the original movie.

801
00:50:57.846 --> 00:50:59.347
I know.
It's pretty wild.

802
00:50:59.431 --> 00:51:03.017
- Well. you have to call it off.
- Um. okay. I mean. it's Friday.

803
00:51:03.102 --> 00:51:06.029
I'm sure we're not the only party
that's goin' on in Woodsboro.

804
00:51:06.113 --> 00:51:08.156
Where is this circle jerk
gonna take place?

805
00:51:08.440 --> 00:51:12.777
- So who's ready for this Q and A?
- No. no. I really want the location.

806
00:51:12.861 --> 00:51:14.579
You know.
it's kind of an underground thing.

807
00:51:14.603 --> 00:51:16.313
Email invites. pretty secret.

808
00:51:16.957 --> 00:51:18.883
What. you're not gonna tell me?

809
00:51:19.028 --> 00:51:20.554
Really?

810
00:51:20.578 --> 00:51:24.289
We're working together.
Remember?

811
00:51:24.373 --> 00:51:26.249
So you ready for that Q and A?

812
00:51:26.333 --> 00:51:29.044
- Fuck you.
- Let's go.

813
00:51:32.631 --> 00:51:34.382
That was awesome.

814
00:51:36.768 --> 00:51:39.279
I feel like I'm under house arrest.

815
00:51:54.436 --> 00:51:58.248
You know when people say.
"I know how you feel."

816
00:51:58.792 --> 00:52:01.636
but you know they're just saying that
because they really have

817
00:52:01.660 --> 00:52:04.545
no frigging idea how you feel?

818
00:52:06.790 --> 00:52:09.835
I know how you feel.

819
00:52:11.219 --> 00:52:14.722
I... am so sorry about Olivia.

820
00:52:19.678 --> 00:52:22.013
I'm sorry about your publicist.

821
00:52:26.810 --> 00:52:31.648
How do you handle it?
People staring at you all the time?

822
00:52:31.732 --> 00:52:34.025
People stare at me?

823
00:52:35.819 --> 00:52:37.987
I could never handle
that kind of attention.

824
00:52:38.072 --> 00:52:41.826
I just... feel like it would
take over your whole life.

825
00:52:46.914 --> 00:52:49.332
what I do is I...

826
00:52:49.416 --> 00:52:54.128
try not to think about me.

827
00:52:54.213 --> 00:52:58.883
I have people I care about.
I focus on them.

828
00:52:58.967 --> 00:53:02.178
And the rest. it. um.
it works out.

829
00:53:05.224 --> 00:53:07.975
You saved my life last night.

830
00:53:08.060 --> 00:53:11.854
I mean. I know we're family.
but you hardly know me.

831
00:53:11.939 --> 00:53:13.773
Makes me wonder. you know.

832
00:53:13.857 --> 00:53:18.111
if I'd have been brave enough
to do the same thing.

833
00:53:18.595 --> 00:53:21.589
I really hope
you never have to find that out.

834
00:53:25.327 --> 00:53:28.329
Well. if you need me.
you know where to find me.

835
00:53:28.414 --> 00:53:31.708
I'll be up in my cell.
Or. I mean. my room.

836
00:53:55.649 --> 00:53:59.652
Her room's all boarded up.
That's the view from my cell.

837
00:53:59.737 --> 00:54:02.113
It's really weird.

838
00:54:02.197 --> 00:54:03.740
I think Olivia
would understand. okay?

839
00:54:03.824 --> 00:54:05.992
She'd want me to be
around other people.

840
00:54:06.437 --> 00:54:07.971
Holy shit.

841
00:54:07.995 --> 00:54:10.747
Even if I did just crash-land
on Planet Dork.

842
00:54:12.091 --> 00:54:14.018
Speaking of which.
Trevor's here.

843
00:54:14.042 --> 00:54:15.543
- What?
- Hey. Kirby.

844
00:54:15.627 --> 00:54:17.920
What is he doing there?
That is so not his scene.

845
00:54:18.005 --> 00:54:20.715
I have no idea.
Maybe he thought you would be here.

846
00:54:20.799 --> 00:54:22.925
Yeah. fat chance.
After what happened last night?

847
00:54:23.010 --> 00:54:25.470
I mean. my mom
is just completely freaked out.

848
00:54:25.554 --> 00:54:26.971
- It's not pretty.
- All right. look.

849
00:54:27.055 --> 00:54:30.057
You go do your "good girl" thing.
and I will drink for the both of us.

850
00:54:30.142 --> 00:54:34.771
- I will keep you posted.
- All right. Be safe.

851
00:55:14.019 --> 00:55:17.480
Stab-a-thon!
Stab-a-thon! Stab-a-thon!

852
00:55:17.564 --> 00:55:20.566
Stab-a-thon! Stab-a-thon!

853
00:55:23.111 --> 00:55:25.530
Thank you! Thank you!
Gracias.

854
00:55:27.741 --> 00:55:31.369
Cinema Club thanks you for coming out
for our third annual Stab-a-thon.

855
00:55:31.453 --> 00:55:33.037
Safety in numbers. my friends!

856
00:55:33.121 --> 00:55:35.832
Who's ready to drink every time
someone can't get a cell phone signal?

857
00:55:37.376 --> 00:55:40.211
Who's ready to drink every time
someone shuts the refrigerator door.

858
00:55:40.295 --> 00:55:42.630
and oh. my God. there's a harmless
character right behind it?

859
00:55:44.633 --> 00:55:47.134
Who's ready to drink every time
someone screams the word...

860
00:55:47.219 --> 00:55:48.636
No!

861
00:55:48.720 --> 00:55:51.597
So let's get
this Stab-a-thon started!

862
00:56:06.822 --> 00:56:10.283
- Hey. watch it!
- Get out of the way!

863
00:56:10.367 --> 00:56:14.370
- Down in front!
- Move your ass!

864
00:56:14.705 --> 00:56:19.625
Screw you!

865
00:56:52.276 --> 00:56:54.336
Yes.

866
00:56:59.794 --> 00:57:03.639
Oh. yeah.
Back on my game.

867
00:57:03.863 --> 00:57:05.189
Perfect.

868
00:57:05.213 --> 00:57:07.924
New work-in-progress.
chapter one.

869
00:57:08.008 --> 00:57:11.636
When I moved to Woodsboro.
I never in a million years dreamed

870
00:57:11.720 --> 00:57:14.931
that I would again play
the critical role

871
00:57:14.955 --> 00:57:17.874
in solving another series of these...

872
00:57:18.018 --> 00:57:19.644
What?

873
00:57:25.525 --> 00:57:27.610
What the hell?

874
00:57:50.258 --> 00:57:51.968
Gale. where are you?

875
00:57:52.052 --> 00:57:54.345
I followed the kids
to the Stab-a-thon.

876
00:57:54.429 --> 00:57:57.473
There's an old abandoned farm
on Fort Dillon Road.

877
00:57:57.557 --> 00:57:58.975
Listen. I've got it
under surveillance.

878
00:57:59.059 --> 00:58:01.394
and I... I think the killer's
about to make his move.

879
00:58:01.478 --> 00:58:03.104
What makes you so sure?

880
00:58:03.748 --> 00:58:06.125
You do a remake
to out-do the original.

881
00:58:06.149 --> 00:58:07.675
that's what the kids said.

882
00:58:07.679 --> 00:58:09.639
This party
is all about the "Stab" movies.

883
00:58:09.703 --> 00:58:12.038
Come on!
How meta can you get?

884
00:58:12.322 --> 00:58:14.407
How "what-a" can you get?

885
00:58:14.491 --> 00:58:16.534
I don't know.
I heard them say it.

886
00:58:16.618 --> 00:58:19.178
Dewey. listen to me.
you have to get out here.

887
00:58:19.202 --> 00:58:21.703
Come on. you catch the killer.
I get the story.

888
00:58:21.748 --> 00:58:22.915
It's a win-win.

889
00:58:23.000 --> 00:58:25.501
Well. I thought
you were going rogue. Gale.

890
00:58:25.585 --> 00:58:28.587
Oh. co... are you serious?
Come on!

891
00:58:28.672 --> 00:58:31.674
Forget it.
Thanks for having faith in me.

892
00:58:31.758 --> 00:58:33.759
I gotta fix my equipment.

893
00:58:33.844 --> 00:58:35.052
Gale!

894
00:58:37.431 --> 00:58:38.556
Shit.

895
00:58:45.772 --> 00:58:47.982
Why don't you get
more comfortable. baby?!

896
00:58:54.049 --> 00:58:56.259
Bravo.
Well... very well done.

897
00:58:56.283 --> 00:58:58.117
Very. I'm very impressed.

898
00:58:58.201 --> 00:59:01.454
I mean. kind... kind of impressed.
Not really.

899
00:59:01.538 --> 00:59:02.705
- That'll do.
- Yeah?

900
00:59:02.789 --> 00:59:04.206
- Yeah.
- Yeah. she wants it. right?

901
00:59:13.098 --> 00:59:15.308
Ghostface! Yeah!

902
00:59:18.972 --> 00:59:20.181
Don't answer it!

903
00:59:22.267 --> 00:59:25.853
- Hello?
- Hello.

904
00:59:25.937 --> 00:59:27.396
Who is this?

905
00:59:27.481 --> 00:59:29.148
Were you expecting somebody?

906
00:59:29.232 --> 00:59:30.608
No.

907
00:59:38.075 --> 00:59:40.034
You know. I don't even know you.

908
00:59:40.118 --> 00:59:41.535
and I dislike you already.

909
00:59:41.620 --> 00:59:43.913
Hicks. how far are you
from Fort Dillon Road?

910
00:59:43.997 --> 00:59:46.415
- Five minutes at the most. sir.
- Well. step on it.

911
00:59:48.460 --> 00:59:50.294
Look out your window.

912
01:00:35.132 --> 01:00:38.175
Gale!
Gale. behind you!

913
01:00:54.067 --> 01:00:56.026
Gale!

914
01:01:10.333 --> 01:01:11.542
Freeze!

915
01:01:25.307 --> 01:01:28.017
Get out of the way.
you morons!

916
01:01:32.655 --> 01:01:34.164
Damn it.

917
01:01:37.204 --> 01:01:39.297
Okay. put pressure on that.

918
01:01:39.321 --> 01:01:40.897
Did you catch him?

919
01:01:40.921 --> 01:01:43.656
No. Hopefully your cameras
caught something.

920
01:01:43.700 --> 01:01:46.202
- They weren't the only ones Dewey.
- What?

921
01:01:46.286 --> 01:01:48.662
There's a webcam that's hidden
up there.

922
01:01:48.747 --> 01:01:51.874
- It was watching me.
- A webcam?

923
01:01:51.958 --> 01:01:53.751
He's recording the murders.

924
01:01:53.835 --> 01:01:55.002
What?

925
01:01:55.086 --> 01:01:58.589
This time...
he's making the movie.

926
01:02:03.362 --> 01:02:07.825
Sidney Prescott detail. man.
I don't... like it.

927
01:02:07.849 --> 01:02:10.952
The cops guarding the house.
they always get it.

928
01:02:11.436 --> 01:02:14.271
- What are you talkin' about?
- It's a movie cop rule.

929
01:02:14.356 --> 01:02:17.858
Sucks to be a cop in a movie.
unless you're Bruce Willis.

930
01:02:17.943 --> 01:02:19.944
Not all cops die in movies.

931
01:02:20.028 --> 01:02:24.573
No. but if it's your last day
before retirement. you do.

932
01:02:24.658 --> 01:02:28.452
If you're a rookie just found out
your wife is pregnant. you do.

933
01:02:28.536 --> 01:02:32.331
Or if your partner's better-looking
than you. you do. and by the way...

934
01:02:32.415 --> 01:02:33.791
I win that one.

935
01:02:35.669 --> 01:02:37.378
You know what?
I'll take the next perimeter.

936
01:02:37.462 --> 01:02:39.588
I'll be right back.

937
01:02:40.733 --> 01:02:43.819
Shit.
I know this one.

938
01:02:43.843 --> 01:02:45.469
You're not supposed to say that.
are you?

939
01:02:45.553 --> 01:02:46.929
Eh. new decade. new rules.

940
01:02:47.013 --> 01:02:49.765
You know. these days.
you might come back. find me dead.

941
01:02:49.849 --> 01:02:52.017
eyes gouged out.
tongue sticking out.

942
01:02:52.102 --> 01:02:54.436
- Could go either way.
- I gotta learn this shit.

943
01:02:55.521 --> 01:02:57.748
I'll take this one.

944
01:02:59.033 --> 01:03:00.601
Hey. Hoss.

945
01:03:01.246 --> 01:03:02.672
Be careful.

946
01:03:02.696 --> 01:03:04.613
I'm always careful.

947
01:03:08.159 --> 01:03:10.494
Dead man walking.

948
01:03:59.919 --> 01:04:03.005
Perkins. was there a window open
on your last perimeter check?

949
01:04:06.051 --> 01:04:08.627
Perkins. come in. over.

950
01:04:38.416 --> 01:04:41.085
Anthony?

951
01:04:41.169 --> 01:04:44.505
Perkins?

952
01:04:47.528 --> 01:04:48.972
Damn it.

953
01:04:48.996 --> 01:04:51.465
You should've seen the look
on your face. rookie.

954
01:04:53.449 --> 01:04:54.825
Hoss!

955
01:04:54.849 --> 01:04:56.459
What the fuck?

956
01:04:57.943 --> 01:05:00.120
Oh. shit.

957
01:05:27.215 --> 01:05:30.467
Fuck Bruce Willis.

958
01:05:57.662 --> 01:06:01.206
Sorry!
The wind chimes were over here.

959
01:06:01.291 --> 01:06:04.334
That was me.
I was trying to fix 'em. sorry.

960
01:06:04.679 --> 01:06:06.772
I'm just back from the store.

961
01:06:06.957 --> 01:06:08.566
You're shopping?

962
01:06:08.590 --> 01:06:11.508
My stress buster.
Got one more bag in the car.

963
01:06:11.593 --> 01:06:13.110
Be right back.

964
01:06:39.162 --> 01:06:41.872
Jill? You gonna get that?

965
01:06:44.167 --> 01:06:46.168
Roberts residence.

966
01:06:46.252 --> 01:06:48.462
You're a survivor.
aren't you. Sidney?

967
01:06:48.546 --> 01:06:51.673
Your one and only skill.
You survive.

968
01:06:51.758 --> 01:06:54.092
I have one question for you.

969
01:06:54.177 --> 01:06:56.770
What good's it to be a survivor
in this little drama

970
01:06:56.794 --> 01:06:59.003
if everyone close to you is dead?

971
01:06:59.349 --> 01:07:02.017
- Who are you?
- Turn on the TV to channel 6.

972
01:07:02.101 --> 01:07:03.644
Who the fuck are you?

973
01:07:03.650 --> 01:07:06.027
Turn it on.
Watch the teaser.

974
01:07:07.190 --> 01:07:10.984
...nearly turned deadly tonight
with the latest victims of these attacks

975
01:07:11.069 --> 01:07:14.655
being the wife of the
Woodsboro sheriff. Gale Riley.

976
01:07:14.739 --> 01:07:19.034
AKA Gale Weathers who's in serious
condition tonight after being stabbed.

977
01:07:19.118 --> 01:07:22.246
Her assailant then disappeared
in a sea of identic...

978
01:07:22.690 --> 01:07:25.976
Glad you came home. Sidney?
Has it been worth it yet?

979
01:07:26.000 --> 01:07:28.502
- Why are you doing this?
- Ah. friends count.

980
01:07:28.586 --> 01:07:31.922
But it's the family ties that cut deep.

981
01:07:32.006 --> 01:07:33.632
Am I right?

982
01:07:33.716 --> 01:07:35.133
What do you mean?

983
01:07:35.218 --> 01:07:37.094
The ones you care about most.

984
01:07:37.118 --> 01:07:40.579
And what's closer than family?
The bond of blood.

985
01:07:40.723 --> 01:07:42.733
- Don't.
- You can't save them.

986
01:07:42.757 --> 01:07:46.302
All you can do is watch.

987
01:07:46.646 --> 01:07:47.854
Jill!

988
01:07:58.324 --> 01:08:00.409
Come on. come on...

989
01:08:06.249 --> 01:08:07.541
Kate?

990
01:08:07.625 --> 01:08:09.334
- Sid?
- Jill's not in her room.

991
01:08:09.419 --> 01:08:10.877
- Oh. my God.
- She's gone to Kirby's.

992
01:08:10.962 --> 01:08:12.337
You gotta call her
and get her back here.

993
01:08:12.341 --> 01:08:13.692
Okay.

994
01:08:14.757 --> 01:08:16.008
Come on. Jill.

995
01:08:16.092 --> 01:08:18.427
- Leave a message.
- She's not picking up.

996
01:08:18.511 --> 01:08:20.596
- What's going on?
- The killer called.

997
01:08:20.680 --> 01:08:23.056
He's coming after me.
but he wants my family first.

998
01:08:23.141 --> 01:08:24.933
- Oh. God. Jill!
- Let's get the cops.

999
01:08:25.018 --> 01:08:26.602
- The cops aren't there.
- What?

1000
01:08:26.686 --> 01:08:28.979
They were there when I first came in.
but they're not there now.

1001
01:08:29.063 --> 01:08:31.356
Let's get to Kirby's.

1002
01:08:34.652 --> 01:08:35.861
Out the front.

1003
01:08:44.078 --> 01:08:46.788
Brace it from the bottom.
Can you?

1004
01:08:51.544 --> 01:08:53.837
Let's get outta here.

1005
01:08:54.581 --> 01:08:56.625
Kate. come on!

1006
01:08:56.949 --> 01:08:58.308
Kate?

1007
01:09:08.811 --> 01:09:12.481
Tell Jill... I'm so... sorry.

1008
01:09:25.186 --> 01:09:26.670
Kate?

1009
01:09:41.761 --> 01:09:44.554
Hicks?
What are you doing?

1010
01:09:44.639 --> 01:09:47.024
I just saw somebody coming around
the side of the house.

1011
01:09:47.048 --> 01:09:49.007
Where are Hoss and Perkins?
I couldn't get them on the radio.

1012
01:09:50.412 --> 01:09:52.105
Whose blood is that?

1013
01:09:52.289 --> 01:09:54.867
It's... it's Kate's.
We were just attacked.

1014
01:09:55.191 --> 01:09:57.109
- She's dead.
- Where is she?

1015
01:09:57.193 --> 01:09:59.236
- Front door.
- Show me.

1016
01:09:59.320 --> 01:10:00.362
Okay.

1017
01:10:04.492 --> 01:10:07.077
- Stay here.
- Okay.

1018
01:10:11.582 --> 01:10:13.750
This is Deputy Hicks.

1019
01:10:13.835 --> 01:10:16.086
I've got a homicide
at the Roberts residence.

1020
01:10:16.170 --> 01:10:19.089
- No sign of Perkins or Hoss.
- Copy that. we'll try to locate them.

1021
01:10:19.173 --> 01:10:22.467
I'm so sorry...

1022
01:10:27.140 --> 01:10:29.307
Hey!

1023
01:10:29.392 --> 01:10:31.935
Halt!

1024
01:10:32.019 --> 01:10:35.647
You're gonna be fine. all right?
I swear.

1025
01:10:35.732 --> 01:10:37.357
No more "on your own."

1026
01:10:37.442 --> 01:10:39.067
It's you and me. forever.

1027
01:10:39.152 --> 01:10:41.403
One. two. three.

1028
01:10:41.487 --> 01:10:43.013
Easy.

1029
01:10:43.698 --> 01:10:45.741
- Dewey?
- Yeah?

1030
01:10:47.386 --> 01:10:49.046
Promise me somethin'.

1031
01:10:49.070 --> 01:10:50.553
Anything.

1032
01:10:51.237 --> 01:10:53.531
Catch that motherfucker.

1033
01:10:54.316 --> 01:10:56.193
Absolutely. I love you.

1034
01:10:56.277 --> 01:10:58.445
I love you.

1035
01:11:00.129 --> 01:11:02.499
You missed chaos.
Utter chaos.

1036
01:11:02.884 --> 01:11:05.844
- I can't believe that.
- The sheriff's wife. man!

1037
01:11:05.928 --> 01:11:07.971
She told us to cancel it.
and we didn't. and now this?

1038
01:11:08.055 --> 01:11:09.765
- What are we supposed to do?
- Robbie. calm down.

1039
01:11:09.849 --> 01:11:12.350
It makes sense.
This is what the re-boots do.

1040
01:11:12.435 --> 01:11:14.144
They... they one-up the original ending.

1041
01:11:14.228 --> 01:11:17.397
The Woodsboro Murders ended at a party.
So in the remake...

1042
01:11:17.482 --> 01:11:20.108
The party's the false ending.
New rules.

1043
01:11:20.193 --> 01:11:22.068
Exactly.

1044
01:11:22.153 --> 01:11:24.404
Okay. no offense. guys.
but I'm gonna put in "Stab 7."

1045
01:11:24.489 --> 01:11:26.299
Nobody cancels my film festival.

1046
01:11:26.883 --> 01:11:29.409
I don't wanna watch that.
not after what happened to Olivia.

1047
01:11:29.494 --> 01:11:31.661
Oh. come on.
it was her favorite.

1048
01:11:31.746 --> 01:11:34.831
Oh. wow. Kirby.
You got some classics here.

1049
01:11:34.916 --> 01:11:37.375
- Yup.
- "Suspiria." "Don't Look Now."

1050
01:11:37.460 --> 01:11:38.802
You know it.

1051
01:11:38.826 --> 01:11:41.403
I could trivia your ass
under the table. Cinema Boy.

1052
01:11:41.547 --> 01:11:44.382
Oh. yeah?
Who played Leatherface first?

1053
01:11:44.467 --> 01:11:49.054
- Gunnar Hansen.
- Wow. Did you feel that?

1054
01:11:49.138 --> 01:11:51.890
That charge that moved
between us just then?

1055
01:11:51.974 --> 01:11:55.018
Oh. that was me.
I have powers.

1056
01:11:55.102 --> 01:11:56.686
So sexy.

1057
01:11:57.132 --> 01:12:00.167
You guys are unbelievable.
You're playing fuckin' trivia games?

1058
01:12:00.191 --> 01:12:02.818
The cops are gonna come for us.
They're gonna shut down my website.

1059
01:12:02.902 --> 01:12:04.653
- We're so dead!
- Yeah. I agree.

1060
01:12:04.737 --> 01:12:07.781
- Jesus Christ. where'd you come from?
- The front door.

1061
01:12:07.865 --> 01:12:09.908
By the way. Kirby. with everything
that's going on right now.

1062
01:12:09.992 --> 01:12:12.836
you probably shouldn't
leave that unlocked.

1063
01:12:13.380 --> 01:12:14.973
Sorry.

1064
01:12:14.997 --> 01:12:18.500
And. um. may I ask
what the hell you're doing here?

1065
01:12:18.584 --> 01:12:21.294
What?
Didn't I find the after-party?

1066
01:12:21.379 --> 01:12:24.297
No. you found the anti-party.
and it's invitation only.

1067
01:12:24.382 --> 01:12:27.592
Yeah. well. I got an invitation.
From Jill.

1068
01:12:29.762 --> 01:12:33.807
- So. what's the story?
- W... What?

1069
01:12:33.891 --> 01:12:38.311
You sent me a text message.
"After-party at Kirby's house."

1070
01:12:38.396 --> 01:12:42.858
- I mean. it was from your phone.
- What do you mean from my phone?

1071
01:12:42.942 --> 01:12:45.986
Where is my phone?
I think I left it in your car.

1072
01:12:46.070 --> 01:12:50.574
I didn't text him.
I didn't text you.

1073
01:12:50.658 --> 01:12:53.159
And I'll prove it.

1074
01:12:53.244 --> 01:12:56.121
So. Charlie. Robbie.

1075
01:12:56.205 --> 01:12:59.249
How's it feel to be an
accessories to a crime. huh?

1076
01:12:59.333 --> 01:13:01.751
I mean. really. Dewey's wife?

1077
01:13:01.836 --> 01:13:02.961
My life is over.

1078
01:13:03.045 --> 01:13:06.006
So which one of you guys sent me
a text message from Jill's phone. huh?

1079
01:13:09.000 --> 01:13:11.628
We're just supposed to accept
that you're telling the truth?

1080
01:13:12.112 --> 01:13:14.198
Isn't your phone missing?

1081
01:13:14.682 --> 01:13:16.933
- Got a new one.
- Really.

1082
01:13:17.018 --> 01:13:20.520
Oh.
that's incredibly convenient.

1083
01:13:20.605 --> 01:13:22.814
- Dewey. it's Hicks.
- What's up?

1084
01:13:23.260 --> 01:13:25.544
- Kate Roberts is dead.
- Huh?

1085
01:13:25.568 --> 01:13:27.402
And Sidney fled the scene.

1086
01:13:27.486 --> 01:13:29.654
What?
What happened to Kate?

1087
01:13:29.739 --> 01:13:31.740
She was stabbed just like the others.

1088
01:13:31.824 --> 01:13:34.701
- What about Jill?
- No sign of her at all.

1089
01:13:34.785 --> 01:13:36.953
Where the hell
were Hoss and Perkins?

1090
01:13:37.038 --> 01:13:39.956
They were found dead
in their car two blocks away.

1091
01:13:40.941 --> 01:13:43.401
Multiple stab wounds.

1092
01:13:43.586 --> 01:13:45.545
Okay.

1093
01:13:45.630 --> 01:13:47.339
I'm on my way.

1094
01:13:47.423 --> 01:13:48.965
Yes. sir.

1095
01:13:55.723 --> 01:13:58.767
Wrong number.

1096
01:13:58.851 --> 01:14:00.644
- Who was that?
- Oh. nobody.

1097
01:14:00.728 --> 01:14:03.813
- Did you pick a movie?
- Yeah. We're gonna go scary.

1098
01:14:03.898 --> 01:14:06.441
- "Saw 4."
- Ugh. I saw that in theaters.

1099
01:14:06.525 --> 01:14:08.818
It sucks.
It's not scary. it's gross...

1100
01:14:34.428 --> 01:14:36.763
Charlie. you want to sit
over here next to me?

1101
01:14:36.847 --> 01:14:39.224
All right.

1102
01:14:43.896 --> 01:14:49.901
All right. get ready for a "Hall Pass"
with Robbie Mercer extra.

1103
01:14:49.986 --> 01:14:54.322
Now tonight. there is a good chance
that Charlie Walker.

1104
01:14:54.407 --> 01:14:59.077
yes. my Charlie Walker.
may get lucky with a girl.

1105
01:14:59.161 --> 01:15:04.082
Now I'm unable to. uh.
divulge my exact location. however.

1106
01:15:04.166 --> 01:15:10.922
suffice it to say. Woodsboro High
may be in store for some geek history.

1107
01:15:11.007 --> 01:15:12.759
We'll see.

1108
01:15:26.564 --> 01:15:27.605
Hello?

1109
01:15:30.526 --> 01:15:32.277
Who's there?

1110
01:15:37.408 --> 01:15:39.367
Oh. my God...

1111
01:15:52.965 --> 01:15:56.009
- Where are you going?
- To make sure the front door is locked.

1112
01:15:57.970 --> 01:16:00.388
No. Don't open it...

1113
01:16:03.434 --> 01:16:06.603
- Hey. Charlie?
- Yeah?

1114
01:16:06.687 --> 01:16:10.982
I'm sorry. I know you're into
the movie and all.

1115
01:16:11.067 --> 01:16:14.027
but now would be a really
good time to make a move.

1116
01:16:15.362 --> 01:16:17.906
For... me to make a move?

1117
01:16:19.950 --> 01:16:22.869
Couldn't you make a move?

1118
01:16:22.953 --> 01:16:25.121
I just did.

1119
01:16:25.206 --> 01:16:28.666
'Cause you're actually pretty cute.

1120
01:16:28.751 --> 01:16:34.506
Especially when I'm scared and...
lonely... and drunk.

1121
01:16:37.426 --> 01:16:40.887
Hey. guys. did...
did you see Jill come in?

1122
01:16:40.971 --> 01:16:43.056
I didn't see her outside.

1123
01:16:43.140 --> 01:16:45.558
Yes. Trevor. she is upstairs.

1124
01:16:45.643 --> 01:16:49.270
Thank God you're here to protect her
when you can't even find her.

1125
01:16:49.355 --> 01:16:51.856
There's nobody out here.

1126
01:16:51.941 --> 01:16:54.943
Oh. dude.
I love this part of the movie.

1127
01:16:55.027 --> 01:16:56.694
Yeah. yeah. yeah.

1128
01:16:56.779 --> 01:17:01.116
Just when you think they're all safe
and comfortable in the house...

1129
01:17:01.200 --> 01:17:03.284
Ghostface comes in.
and. bam!

1130
01:17:07.373 --> 01:17:09.958
Did I just interrupt something
right here?

1131
01:17:10.042 --> 01:17:14.129
Shut the fuck up.

1132
01:17:14.213 --> 01:17:16.381
Who invited you. Trevor?!

1133
01:17:16.465 --> 01:17:19.926
All right. Clearly not you.

1134
01:17:20.010 --> 01:17:23.721
Wow. I'm gonna be upstairs.

1135
01:17:23.806 --> 01:17:26.432
Get out of my house!

1136
01:17:28.561 --> 01:17:30.979
Yeah. yeah.

1137
01:17:31.063 --> 01:17:34.732
Okay. I'm a little drunk.
so don't blame your internet connection.

1138
01:17:34.817 --> 01:17:38.570
Let's see
what Charlie's up to. shall we?

1139
01:17:38.654 --> 01:17:41.823
Or the saga of Trevor and Jill.

1140
01:17:41.907 --> 01:17:43.741
Oh. the intrigue of Woodsboro High.

1141
01:17:43.826 --> 01:17:46.327
Who needs a killer around
when there's so much drama?

1142
01:18:00.658 --> 01:18:02.535
Oh. man.

1143
01:18:04.972 --> 01:18:06.389
That's better.

1144
01:18:20.946 --> 01:18:23.573
Wait. no. you can't!
You can't! There's rules!

1145
01:18:23.657 --> 01:18:25.658
I... I'm gay! I'm gay!

1146
01:18:25.743 --> 01:18:28.661
I mean. if it helps.

1147
01:18:35.169 --> 01:18:37.337
...random girl who gets a call

1148
01:18:37.421 --> 01:18:38.922
that undoubtedly ends up
getting her killed.

1149
01:18:39.006 --> 01:18:41.257
It's all so predictable.
There's no element of surprise.

1150
01:18:41.342 --> 01:18:42.800
You can see ev...

1151
01:18:56.941 --> 01:18:58.191
Kirby!

1152
01:18:58.275 --> 01:19:00.526
I found my phone.
It was up in your room.

1153
01:19:00.611 --> 01:19:02.612
There was no text message
sent to Trevor.

1154
01:19:02.696 --> 01:19:07.116
He is such a liar.
Where is he?

1155
01:19:07.201 --> 01:19:10.453
What do you mean where is he?
He just went upstairs looking for you.

1156
01:19:10.537 --> 01:19:13.456
He's not upstairs.

1157
01:19:13.540 --> 01:19:14.832
Trevor?

1158
01:19:17.127 --> 01:19:19.963
Charlie? Robbie?

1159
01:19:20.047 --> 01:19:22.257
Maybe they're outside.

1160
01:19:22.341 --> 01:19:23.549
Jill.

1161
01:19:23.634 --> 01:19:25.760
Sidney. I... I'm sorry. I should've told
you and Mom where I was going...

1162
01:19:25.844 --> 01:19:28.096
No. it's okay. It's just.
I... I need you to come with me.

1163
01:19:28.180 --> 01:19:30.190
Come with me right now. okay?

1164
01:19:31.934 --> 01:19:33.102
Run.

1165
01:19:33.126 --> 01:19:34.535
Robbie!

1166
01:19:37.773 --> 01:19:38.982
Go!

1167
01:19:41.151 --> 01:19:44.570
Sidney!

1168
01:19:44.655 --> 01:19:45.863
Come on!

1169
01:19:49.243 --> 01:19:51.828
- The balcony!
- There's no other way out?

1170
01:19:51.912 --> 01:19:54.055
We can jump.

1171
01:19:54.540 --> 01:19:57.000
It's two stories.
Where's your cell?

1172
01:19:57.084 --> 01:19:58.334
- Uh. here.
- Get under the bed!

1173
01:19:58.419 --> 01:20:00.253
- What?
- Just do what I say! Get under the bed.

1174
01:20:00.337 --> 01:20:02.130
Don't make a sound and don't come out
until I come get you. okay?

1175
01:20:02.214 --> 01:20:04.340
- Just trust me.
- Okay.

1176
01:20:11.432 --> 01:20:14.350
You got it? You're okay?
Jill. run!

1177
01:20:14.435 --> 01:20:16.436
Just keep running. get help!

1178
01:20:41.253 --> 01:20:42.795
- Hello?
- Dewey!

1179
01:20:42.880 --> 01:20:45.089
- Sidney. where are you?
- I'm at Kirby's.

1180
01:20:45.174 --> 01:20:46.674
The killer is here.
I need your help.

1181
01:20:46.759 --> 01:20:48.676
- I'm on my way.
- Okay.

1182
01:20:51.096 --> 01:20:53.181
Sidney? Sidney!

1183
01:20:53.265 --> 01:20:56.017
I need all units to 329
Whispering Lane.

1184
01:20:56.101 --> 01:20:58.478
All units.
329 Whispering Lane!

1185
01:21:18.540 --> 01:21:19.624
Sorry. It's just me.

1186
01:21:19.708 --> 01:21:22.126
Look. I tried to call 911.
but the landline's dead.

1187
01:21:22.211 --> 01:21:24.796
- ...and someone smashed the router.
- I think I got through on my cell.

1188
01:21:24.880 --> 01:21:27.006
Where's Jill?

1189
01:21:27.030 --> 01:21:29.157
Oh. God.
Go. go. go. go.

1190
01:21:33.222 --> 01:21:36.015
There's a room down here.
We can lock ourselves in.

1191
01:21:36.100 --> 01:21:38.393
I heard you yelling to Jill.
Did she get away?

1192
01:21:38.477 --> 01:21:40.019
I think she's safe.

1193
01:21:47.486 --> 01:21:50.947
- Kirby. let me in!
- Charlie.

1194
01:21:52.091 --> 01:21:54.010
No. No. no. no. no.

1195
01:21:54.034 --> 01:21:55.993
I just found Robbie.
This... this is his blood.

1196
01:21:56.078 --> 01:21:58.746
Please. Please.
There is someone else out here.

1197
01:21:58.831 --> 01:21:59.914
Let me in!

1198
01:21:59.998 --> 01:22:01.958
If you can't trust him.
don't open the door.

1199
01:22:03.102 --> 01:22:05.188
My God. let me in!

1200
01:22:05.212 --> 01:22:06.546
Get away from the door.
Charlie.

1201
01:22:06.630 --> 01:22:08.673
Kirby. it is me.
Please let me in!

1202
01:22:08.757 --> 01:22:10.842
Get away from the door.
Charlie.

1203
01:22:10.926 --> 01:22:13.219
It's me!

1204
01:22:13.303 --> 01:22:16.055
I'm sorry. I can't.

1205
01:22:16.140 --> 01:22:19.475
- What the fuck?!
- I'm sorry.

1206
01:22:19.560 --> 01:22:21.352
Behind you! Look out!

1207
01:22:24.898 --> 01:22:26.566
No! No. no. no!

1208
01:22:26.650 --> 01:22:29.402
Kirby!

1209
01:22:40.255 --> 01:22:41.923
Oh. God. no. please.

1210
01:22:42.047 --> 01:22:45.216
Leave him alone!

1211
01:22:47.880 --> 01:22:50.882
It's Charlie's phone.

1212
01:22:50.966 --> 01:22:54.469
Tell Sidney heads
are gonna roll tonight.

1213
01:22:54.553 --> 01:22:56.304
Tell Sidney
it's all because of her.

1214
01:22:56.388 --> 01:23:01.058
Or maybe she wants to take his place.
I promise to be quick.

1215
01:23:01.143 --> 01:23:03.352
- It's him.
- Okay. okay. I'm gonna get Jill.

1216
01:23:03.437 --> 01:23:05.646
We should be in the same place.
Just... just keep him on the phone.

1217
01:23:05.731 --> 01:23:08.066
I'll be right back. okay?

1218
01:23:09.151 --> 01:23:11.486
Let him go. please.

1219
01:23:11.570 --> 01:23:13.863
I hear you like horror movies.
Kirby.

1220
01:23:13.947 --> 01:23:16.532
But do you like 'em
as much as him?

1221
01:23:16.617 --> 01:23:19.702
Forget watching "Stab."
You get to live it.

1222
01:23:19.786 --> 01:23:23.247
No. no. no. no. no!
He's the expert! It's not me!

1223
01:23:23.332 --> 01:23:25.583
Warm-up question:
Jason's weapon?

1224
01:23:25.667 --> 01:23:27.835
Uh. it's a machete.

1225
01:23:27.920 --> 01:23:31.088
There. you see?
You do know the genre.

1226
01:23:31.173 --> 01:23:34.133
- Michael Myers?
- Uh. butcher knife.

1227
01:23:34.218 --> 01:23:37.011
- Leatherface?
- A chainsaw. Please!

1228
01:23:37.095 --> 01:23:38.304
Just ask Sidney
if you need some help.

1229
01:23:38.388 --> 01:23:40.890
- Freddy Krueger?!
- Uh. uh. razor hands.

1230
01:23:40.974 --> 01:23:43.434
Name the movie that started
the slasher craze.

1231
01:23:43.519 --> 01:23:46.354
"Halloween." "Texas Chainsaw Massacre."
"Last House on the Left." or "Psycho"?

1232
01:23:46.438 --> 01:23:49.023
- "Psycho"!
- None of the above!

1233
01:23:49.107 --> 01:23:51.442
"Peeping Tom." 1960.
directed by Michael Powell.

1234
01:23:51.527 --> 01:23:54.654
First movie to ever put the audience
in the killer's POV.

1235
01:23:54.738 --> 01:23:56.906
What? Wait.
No. no. no.

1236
01:23:56.990 --> 01:23:59.742
Please. just ask me one more question!
Just one more!

1237
01:23:59.826 --> 01:24:02.119
All right. Kirby.

1238
01:24:02.204 --> 01:24:05.540
Then it's time
for your last-chance question.

1239
01:24:05.624 --> 01:24:10.503
Name the remake of the groundbreaking
horror movie in which the villain...

1240
01:24:10.587 --> 01:24:13.256
Uh. "Halloween." uh. "Texas Chainsaw."
"Dawn Of The Dead."

1241
01:24:13.340 --> 01:24:15.758
"The Hills Have Eyes."
"Amityville Horror."

1242
01:24:15.842 --> 01:24:18.261
uh. "Last House On The Left."
"Friday The Thirteenth."

1243
01:24:18.345 --> 01:24:20.680
"A Nightmare On Elm Street."
"My Bloody Valentine."

1244
01:24:20.764 --> 01:24:23.808
"When A Stranger Calls."
"Prom Night." "Black Christmas."

1245
01:24:23.892 --> 01:24:28.145
"House Of Wax." "The Fog."
uh. "Piranha."

1246
01:24:28.230 --> 01:24:31.107
It's one of those. right?
Right?

1247
01:24:37.833 --> 01:24:40.009
I got it right.

1248
01:24:40.033 --> 01:24:41.909
I was fucking right.

1249
01:24:41.994 --> 01:24:43.411
Jill?

1250
01:24:55.424 --> 01:24:57.842
I won. Charlie.
I fucking won.

1251
01:24:57.926 --> 01:25:01.053
I won. He tried to beat me.
but I fucking won.

1252
01:25:01.138 --> 01:25:03.097
Great. Kirby.

1253
01:25:03.181 --> 01:25:07.226
Hold on.
Okay. Almost there.

1254
01:25:07.311 --> 01:25:10.271
Just hang tight.
Okay. Okay.

1255
01:25:10.355 --> 01:25:11.814
- All right.
- Kirby?

1256
01:25:11.898 --> 01:25:13.608
- Yeah?
- This is making a move.

1257
01:25:17.195 --> 01:25:19.905
Four years of classes together.
and you notice me now?

1258
01:25:19.990 --> 01:25:22.199
Stupid bitch!

1259
01:25:22.284 --> 01:25:24.577
It's too late!

1260
01:25:26.330 --> 01:25:28.456
Oh. I know. I know.

1261
01:25:28.540 --> 01:25:30.416
It's okay.
Take your time.

1262
01:25:30.500 --> 01:25:32.835
Doesn't happen as fast
as it does in the movies. I know.

1263
01:25:32.919 --> 01:25:36.297
C... Charlie...

1264
01:25:36.381 --> 01:25:38.215
Charlie...

1265
01:26:02.258 --> 01:26:03.591
Kirby?

1266
01:26:07.496 --> 01:26:10.873
You know. you learn a lot when
you watch movies over and over.

1267
01:26:10.957 --> 01:26:13.709
All the plots
are about trying to kill you.

1268
01:26:13.794 --> 01:26:15.461
Where's Jill?

1269
01:26:15.545 --> 01:26:17.755
Oh. you think
she's gonna get away?

1270
01:26:17.839 --> 01:26:19.215
You think anyone gets away?

1271
01:26:29.518 --> 01:26:32.603
- Jill?
- Hello. Sidney.

1272
01:26:32.688 --> 01:26:33.771
Surprised?

1273
01:26:33.855 --> 01:26:35.981
Watch this.

1274
01:26:36.066 --> 01:26:42.571
This is the part. my dear cousin.
when the cameras turn off.

1275
01:26:45.784 --> 01:26:47.410
Charlie?

1276
01:26:47.494 --> 01:26:49.078
Already taken care of.

1277
01:26:49.162 --> 01:26:51.831
Man. I got great footage
of my Robbie kill.

1278
01:26:51.915 --> 01:26:54.125
Better than Jenny
and Marnie or Olivia even.

1279
01:26:54.209 --> 01:26:57.211
Good. we'll cut and upload it later
and make it all traceable to Trevor.

1280
01:26:57.295 --> 01:26:58.921
Speaking of which...

1281
01:27:01.842 --> 01:27:04.719
- Remind you of anything?
- Jill. please...

1282
01:27:04.803 --> 01:27:06.554
Shut up! Dick.

1283
01:27:06.638 --> 01:27:08.180
Everything I learned.
I learned from you.

1284
01:27:08.265 --> 01:27:10.808
You think you had a shitty boyfriend.
Sidney?

1285
01:27:10.892 --> 01:27:16.564
Here's one that fucks you. dumps you.
and doesn't even make you famous.

1286
01:27:16.648 --> 01:27:19.608
What the fuck. Jill?
I loved you!

1287
01:27:19.693 --> 01:27:22.069
Shut the fuck up already!

1288
01:27:24.322 --> 01:27:26.782
I'm sure those cops
would want you to have this. Jill.

1289
01:27:26.867 --> 01:27:28.242
For your protection.

1290
01:27:28.826 --> 01:27:30.252
No.

1291
01:27:32.097 --> 01:27:34.684
Baby. please...
baby. please...

1292
01:27:34.708 --> 01:27:37.001
Shouldn't have killed
all these people. Trev.

1293
01:27:37.085 --> 01:27:39.378
Gone and put it on video even.

1294
01:27:39.463 --> 01:27:41.547
But it means
a lot that you did it for me.

1295
01:27:41.631 --> 01:27:43.758
What the fuck
are you talking about?!

1296
01:27:43.842 --> 01:27:47.511
I am not the girl you cheat on.

1297
01:27:52.017 --> 01:27:54.477
I've gone through everything.
We're definitely good on timeline.

1298
01:27:54.561 --> 01:27:57.229
Oh. yeah.
We're perfect.

1299
01:27:57.314 --> 01:27:59.732
No. no. no. please!

1300
01:28:06.239 --> 01:28:08.365
Ready for act three?

1301
01:28:08.450 --> 01:28:10.910
Got it figured out yet. Sidney?

1302
01:28:10.994 --> 01:28:12.453
In keeping with our remake theme.

1303
01:28:12.537 --> 01:28:15.164
Trevor's this generation's
Billy Loomis.

1304
01:28:15.248 --> 01:28:18.501
and we're the innocent victims.
Sidney and Randy.

1305
01:28:18.585 --> 01:28:22.171
See. with you. the world
just heard about what happened.

1306
01:28:22.255 --> 01:28:25.216
But with us. they're gonna see it.

1307
01:28:25.300 --> 01:28:29.178
It's gonna be a worldwide sensation.
I mean. people gotta see this shit.

1308
01:28:29.262 --> 01:28:32.515
It's not like anyone reads anymore.

1309
01:28:32.599 --> 01:28:38.979
We're gonna know fame
like you never even dreamed of.

1310
01:28:39.064 --> 01:28:41.357
Last two teenagers standing.

1311
01:28:41.441 --> 01:28:44.068
This time Randy gets the girl.

1312
01:28:49.533 --> 01:28:52.409
You were amazing.
You're the perfect victim.

1313
01:28:52.494 --> 01:28:56.080
I was so believable today.
wasn't I?

1314
01:28:56.164 --> 01:29:00.668
I mean. I told so many lies
that I actually started to believe them.

1315
01:29:00.752 --> 01:29:02.962
I really think
that I was born for this.

1316
01:29:03.046 --> 01:29:04.755
How could you do this?

1317
01:29:06.900 --> 01:29:09.987
Do you know what it was like
growing up in this family?

1318
01:29:10.011 --> 01:29:12.346
Related to you?

1319
01:29:12.430 --> 01:29:15.266
I mean. all I ever heard
was Sidney this

1320
01:29:15.350 --> 01:29:18.602
and Sidney that
and Sidney. Sidney. Sidney.

1321
01:29:18.687 --> 01:29:22.147
You were always
just so fucking special!

1322
01:29:22.232 --> 01:29:23.983
Well.
now I'm the special one.

1323
01:29:24.067 --> 01:29:26.318
You'll slip.
They always do.

1324
01:29:26.403 --> 01:29:28.654
Come on. Charlie.
let's get on with this.

1325
01:29:31.783 --> 01:29:36.120
You have to be strong.
And hold still. okay?

1326
01:29:36.204 --> 01:29:39.582
Yeah. Yeah. old school.
like Billy and Stu.

1327
01:29:39.666 --> 01:29:41.792
Come on. baby. get it up!

1328
01:29:41.877 --> 01:29:45.421
Come on. Shoulder me!
Shoulder me! Shoulder me!

1329
01:29:45.505 --> 01:29:47.339
Get it up!

1330
01:29:50.969 --> 01:29:54.305
The heart...
That's not the way we rehearsed it.

1331
01:29:54.389 --> 01:29:58.017
You said it. Charlie.
Billy and Stu. Trevor and you.

1332
01:29:58.101 --> 01:30:03.647
What the media really loves. baby.
is a sole survivor.

1333
01:30:03.732 --> 01:30:05.900
Just ask you-know-who.

1334
01:30:05.984 --> 01:30:10.696
Trevor was your partner.
But you. you were the idea man.

1335
01:30:20.565 --> 01:30:22.858
Even your friends.

1336
01:30:23.603 --> 01:30:25.171
My friends?

1337
01:30:25.195 --> 01:30:27.154
What world are you living in?

1338
01:30:27.339 --> 01:30:29.089
I don't need friends.

1339
01:30:29.374 --> 01:30:31.367
I need fans.

1340
01:30:31.551 --> 01:30:32.968
Don't you get it?!

1341
01:30:33.053 --> 01:30:36.680
This has never been
about killing you.

1342
01:30:36.765 --> 01:30:39.808
It's about...
becoming you.

1343
01:30:39.893 --> 01:30:42.603
I mean. for fuck's sake.
my own mother had to die...

1344
01:30:42.687 --> 01:30:46.565
no great loss there...
so I could stay true to the original.

1345
01:30:46.650 --> 01:30:48.567
That's sick. right?

1346
01:30:48.652 --> 01:30:51.946
Well. sick is the new sane.

1347
01:30:52.030 --> 01:30:53.697
You had your fifteen minutes.

1348
01:30:53.782 --> 01:30:55.532
Now I want mine!

1349
01:30:55.617 --> 01:30:59.119
I mean. what am I supposed to do?
Go to college?

1350
01:30:59.204 --> 01:31:01.705
Grad school? Work?

1351
01:31:01.790 --> 01:31:03.248
Look around.

1352
01:31:03.333 --> 01:31:05.542
We all live in public now.
we're all on the Internet.

1353
01:31:05.627 --> 01:31:08.879
How do you think people
become famous anymore?

1354
01:31:08.964 --> 01:31:12.841
You don't have to achieve anything.

1355
01:31:12.926 --> 01:31:16.095
You just gotta have
fucked-up shit happen to you.

1356
01:31:16.179 --> 01:31:19.139
So. you do have to die. Sid.

1357
01:31:19.224 --> 01:31:23.268
Those are the rules.
New movie. new franchise.

1358
01:31:23.353 --> 01:31:26.021
There's only room for one lead.
and let's face it.

1359
01:31:26.106 --> 01:31:29.108
your ingénue days.
they're over.

1360
01:31:35.448 --> 01:31:37.449
Don't tell me you didn't know
this day would come.

1361
01:32:57.739 --> 01:33:00.032
Oh. fuck!

1362
01:34:20.512 --> 01:34:22.890
Come on. let's move it!

1363
01:34:32.185 --> 01:34:34.103
Check the rooms.
both sides and upstairs.

1364
01:34:34.127 --> 01:34:35.310
Yes. ma'am.

1365
01:34:52.562 --> 01:34:54.771
Jill. can you give us
a description of the murderer?

1366
01:35:08.786 --> 01:35:11.205
Jill! How does it feel to be a hero?

1367
01:35:18.755 --> 01:35:22.507
It's okay.
You're gonna be okay.

1368
01:35:22.592 --> 01:35:26.970
Jill. You made it.
That's all that matters.

1369
01:35:27.055 --> 01:35:29.473
Trevor. Charlie.
they tried to kill me.

1370
01:35:29.557 --> 01:35:34.186
And I heard they killed my mom.
And... and Robbie and Kirby. too.

1371
01:35:34.270 --> 01:35:36.939
Just lay back.

1372
01:35:37.023 --> 01:35:39.816
Try to rest.

1373
01:35:39.901 --> 01:35:41.568
Is... is your wife...

1374
01:35:43.129 --> 01:35:46.924
She's gonna be fine.
She's recovering.

1375
01:35:47.408 --> 01:35:51.536
If I ever write a book one day. I'd...
I'd want her to write it with me.

1376
01:35:51.621 --> 01:35:56.250
We'd be a good team
with our matching wounds and all.

1377
01:35:59.077 --> 01:36:00.955
We're survivors now.

1378
01:36:01.839 --> 01:36:04.549
I just wish Sidney was. too.

1379
01:36:04.634 --> 01:36:06.802
Jill...

1380
01:36:06.886 --> 01:36:08.929
they're not sure yet.

1381
01:36:09.013 --> 01:36:11.473
It's still touch and go.

1382
01:36:11.557 --> 01:36:13.183
But she's in ICU.

1383
01:36:13.268 --> 01:36:17.354
And they think Sidney
just might make it.

1384
01:36:17.438 --> 01:36:19.314
What?

1385
01:36:19.399 --> 01:36:21.650
But... but I saw Trevor kill her.

1386
01:36:21.734 --> 01:36:24.403
Look. we don't know yet.

1387
01:36:24.487 --> 01:36:26.238
But she's hanging on.

1388
01:36:29.492 --> 01:36:31.618
I... I... I wanna see her.

1389
01:36:31.703 --> 01:36:34.454
She's not awake yet.

1390
01:36:34.539 --> 01:36:37.082
And she may not
remember anything.

1391
01:36:37.166 --> 01:36:39.543
You'll to help her with that.

1392
01:36:39.627 --> 01:36:43.005
All in time.
Just get some rest now. okay?

1393
01:36:44.716 --> 01:36:46.258
Your attention. please.

1394
01:36:46.342 --> 01:36:49.928
There will be a mandatory meeting
for all non-emergency personnel

1395
01:36:50.013 --> 01:36:53.098
in the basement conference room
in five minutes.

1396
01:37:08.114 --> 01:37:12.409
There will be a mandatory meeting
for all non-emergency personnel

1397
01:37:12.493 --> 01:37:15.579
in the basement conference room
in five minutes.

1398
01:37:31.888 --> 01:37:34.598
She gonna be okay?

1399
01:37:34.682 --> 01:37:37.351
Yeah. She's a strong kid.

1400
01:37:37.435 --> 01:37:40.103
She's gonna have to be.

1401
01:37:40.188 --> 01:37:43.190
She asked if you were okay.

1402
01:37:43.274 --> 01:37:48.028
She thinks you guys should write a book
together with your matching wounds.

1403
01:37:48.112 --> 01:37:49.988
Why. she was stabbed in the shoulder?

1404
01:37:53.993 --> 01:37:56.036
How did she know I was. too?

1405
01:38:01.467 --> 01:38:03.159
Shit!

1406
01:38:08.883 --> 01:38:10.926
You just won't die. will ya?

1407
01:38:12.271 --> 01:38:13.614
Who are you?

1408
01:38:13.638 --> 01:38:15.514
Michael fucking Myers?

1409
01:38:17.016 --> 01:38:19.017
Yeah. I don't think so.

1410
01:38:23.439 --> 01:38:25.857
Fucking die already!

1411
01:38:48.881 --> 01:38:50.507
How are those stitches?

1412
01:38:55.703 --> 01:38:57.296
Sidney!

1413
01:39:00.560 --> 01:39:03.395
Hicks. get up to Sidney Prescott's room
and call for back-up!

1414
01:39:03.479 --> 01:39:04.980
Be right up. sir!

1415
01:39:13.121 --> 01:39:14.647
Sid!

1416
01:39:15.408 --> 01:39:17.075
- Sid...
- Dewey!

1417
01:39:35.261 --> 01:39:37.554
Is this how it's gonna be.
Sid?

1418
01:39:37.638 --> 01:39:39.723
The ending of the movie
was supposed to be at the house.

1419
01:39:39.807 --> 01:39:42.100
I mean. this is just silly.

1420
01:39:42.185 --> 01:39:45.270
Consider this an alternate ending.

1421
01:39:45.354 --> 01:39:47.689
You're never
gonna get out of this. Jill.

1422
01:39:47.773 --> 01:39:49.566
- Of course I will.
- Dewey!

1423
01:39:49.650 --> 01:39:52.527
Sid?

1424
01:39:52.612 --> 01:39:56.072
Easy. Okay. okay.

1425
01:39:56.157 --> 01:39:57.491
What about the book?

1426
01:39:57.575 --> 01:39:59.868
Looks like
I'll just have to write it myself.

1427
01:40:02.005 --> 01:40:03.422
God damn it!

1428
01:40:04.906 --> 01:40:08.001
Don't even think about shooting
or I'll blow Dewey's head off.

1429
01:40:09.045 --> 01:40:12.298
You think I won't do it?
Gimme your gun!

1430
01:40:12.482 --> 01:40:14.075
Do it.

1431
01:40:23.559 --> 01:40:26.394
You just had to be the hero. huh?

1432
01:40:26.479 --> 01:40:28.146
Gimme your gun.

1433
01:40:30.024 --> 01:40:32.651
What are you. deaf?

1434
01:40:32.735 --> 01:40:35.362
Give me... your gun!

1435
01:40:42.328 --> 01:40:46.122
Now get up.

1436
01:40:46.207 --> 01:40:47.916
And keep your hands
over your head.

1437
01:40:48.000 --> 01:40:49.251
Don't do anything stu...

1438
01:40:50.795 --> 01:40:53.755
Don't fucking tell me what to do.

1439
01:40:53.839 --> 01:40:55.782
Oh. God.

1440
01:40:55.967 --> 01:40:57.509
Now get up. bitch.

1441
01:40:57.653 --> 01:40:59.155
Okay.

1442
01:40:59.479 --> 01:41:00.938
Get up!

1443
01:41:01.722 --> 01:41:04.516
- Now!
- Okay.

1444
01:41:07.600 --> 01:41:09.187
Come on.

1445
01:41:14.860 --> 01:41:18.029
Let's go.
Get your skinny ass out here.

1446
01:41:18.114 --> 01:41:21.199
Okay.

1447
01:41:21.284 --> 01:41:25.370
I'm gonna enjoy
blowing your head off.

1448
01:41:25.454 --> 01:41:29.457
Okay. but can I just...

1449
01:41:29.542 --> 01:41:31.710
have one final word?

1450
01:41:31.794 --> 01:41:33.922
What? "Please"?

1451
01:41:36.007 --> 01:41:37.567
No.

1452
01:41:39.952 --> 01:41:42.028
- Clear.
- "Clear"?

1453
01:41:42.213 --> 01:41:43.588
Clear.

1454
01:41:48.728 --> 01:41:51.021
You forgot
the first rule of remakes. Jill.

1455
01:41:51.105 --> 01:41:53.607
Don't fuck with the original.

1456
01:41:57.644 --> 01:41:59.313
Oh. my God. Dewey.

1457
01:41:59.697 --> 01:42:01.489
What hit me?

1458
01:42:01.574 --> 01:42:03.951
Don't ask.

1459
01:42:05.836 --> 01:42:07.503
You okay?

1460
01:42:09.874 --> 01:42:12.709
She was standing
right behind me.

1461
01:42:13.793 --> 01:42:15.671
They always are.

1462
01:42:28.284 --> 01:42:29.409
Oh. God.

1463
01:42:30.653 --> 01:42:32.247
Nice one.

1464
01:42:33.571 --> 01:42:35.782
Hicks? You're alive?

1465
01:42:37.568 --> 01:42:40.278
Wear the vest.
save your chest.

1466
01:42:42.657 --> 01:42:46.660
We got two officers down.
Several injuries.

1467
01:42:46.744 --> 01:42:50.121
- And a new suspect.
- Sheriff? Sheriff...

1468
01:42:50.206 --> 01:42:53.958
We need a doctor. goddamn it!

1469
01:42:54.043 --> 01:42:56.753
I don't know about you.
but I feel a whole lot better.

1470
01:42:56.837 --> 01:43:00.006
Where the hell is everybody?!

1471
01:43:00.091 --> 01:43:02.309
We're live at Woodsboro Community
Hospital.

1472
01:43:02.393 --> 01:43:06.188
awaiting a first public statement
from Jill Roberts. survivor.

1473
01:43:06.272 --> 01:43:10.734
...a survivor of what is now being
called the Woodsboro Massacre Re-boot.

1474
01:43:10.818 --> 01:43:14.196
Jill Roberts is her name.
a name the whole world will now know.

1475
01:43:14.280 --> 01:43:16.531
...who single-handedly put a stop

1476
01:43:16.616 --> 01:43:19.451
to this 21st-Century
Woodsboro killing spree.

1477
01:43:19.735 --> 01:43:21.695
Jill Roberts of Woodsboro.

1478
01:43:21.779 --> 01:43:24.864
a girl who's lifted
all our spirits tonight.

1479
01:43:24.949 --> 01:43:28.410
an American hero.
right out of the movies.
